This storied cheap eats spot in Chinatown was suggested to me at least a hundred times before I was able to make the trek down and try them out.  I had visited other spots in the area before like Wo Hop, Wah Fung, and some others so I had high expectations when many people said this spot was just as good if not better. We decided to get the dish most suggested to us (the wheat peanut butter noodles) and then also added one we really wanted to try (the pork and chive dumplings).  The woman at the counter was very friendly and spoke good English (which in some spots is surpringly an issue).  For the two dishes and two cans of soda it was only $9! The peanut butter noodles were unlike anything I ve had before.  They did not have a Thai peanut taste really (which is what I was expecting) but they didn t exactly just taste like peanut butter either.  I enjoyed the sauce a great deal.  The noodles also were a great texture.  They were similar to a thin egg noodle but they had longer length similar to any long style pasta like spaghetti or fettuccine.  I would absolutely order these again, and trust when I say that my next trip to Chinatown will have these included. The steamed pork and chive dumplings were also a huge hit.  The filling had excellent flavor, a nice texture to the outer skin, and after you added a little chili oil there were was a lot of dimensions of flavor.  I enjoyed these a lot and I think I d enjoy them just as much if they were pan fried so half had a crust to them.  We had dumplings at other spots on this day and these were my favorite of them all. Trust that we will be back here for sure and will try out some soup and other items as well as get these again.  Shu Jiao Fu Zhou - Didn t Suck!

If I m being honest, I have eaten here probably 10+ times within under a year. The food is SO fresh. I get the wheat peanut noodles and pork and chive dumplings, and it has never gotten old. The prices are just unbeatable, even when you order on a delivery app. In the photo I attached, everything there was $24 together (plus pork buns that weren t pictured). I had four pieces of pork dumplings with a large beef tripe noodle soup. The beef tripe is served in a light broth with the noodles and vegetables. The dumplings were steamed, stuffed with pork, which had a unique flavor.
The food was truly amazing and reasonably priced. We got the peanut noodles ($3), pork buns ($4), steamed chicken chive dumplings ($6.50 for 10) and hot and sour soup. Everything was so delicious.

Not my cup of tea. However I think for the price its worth it. I find that everything is a bit sweet here, perhaps to cater to the western tongue. The dumplings, which they are known for, is way too sweet for my taste in particular. Big disappointment given how much Ive heard about this spot. Still a good deal for the price though. Peanut noodles were nice but also nothing crazy. People are nice and I hope this business continues to thrive. Its probably just not for me. Atmosphere is nice in that there is good seating, but doesnt seem particularly pristine. Again, great budget asian food and i think deserves to be popular for sure. But if you are looking for a particular super authentic taste I dont think this is the right place.

Clockwise from the top left, there are chicken mushroom dumplings (4D), meat intestine thin noodles (1A), pork cheek soup (12), and pork cabbage dumplings (4A). If you like the unique flavor of Chinese food, we recommend the dumplings, and if you want to experience the taste of Korean food, we recommend the meat noodles. The meat noodle soup is almost similar to the Korean galbitang soup, but it would be better to think of it as a little more seasoned.

detailed_reviews.review_text: The food at this place is just amazing. Peanut butter noodles, dumplings, pork bun and won ton soup are the dishes I tried and everything was delicious. (especially the dumplings and the noodles). The best thing is definitely the price!  We ate 4 people for 30 dollars and we almost couldnt finish the amount of food we bought. Most dishes are $3, while the most expensive ones are $5.50, which is impossible in Manhattan for such quality. It is a small place, with some tables, they attend you quickly and give the food in seconds.

Went there for lunch.  Spent 13 dollars on 3 dishes which is a plus.  Got the beef noodle soup which is plain.  The signature peanut sauce noodle got a piece of dish scrubber metal thread in it.  The steam bums were decent for its price.  Basic folding tables and chairs for dine-in.   Its a good place to go if you are scraping for cash otherwise I wont recommend it.

Their steamed pork dumplings, their beef noodle soup, their peanut noodles, their pork filled fish ball soup, their pork buns  They ve really outdone themselves. I ll always keep coming back. ( CASH ONLY) This place is so far my most favorite restaurant in the entire new york city. Literally the best. I love finding under $10 lunch whenever i come to ny for work and this place is the winner. I read reviews on google maps before going to see which menu i should try. I ordered pork&chive dumplings and peanut sauce noodle. (both were $3 each) Who needs to go to a fancy chinese restaurant when you can eat such amazing dishes for this price at this restaurant. I m back in my home country and still can t forget the taste. Will definitely go back next time i m in nyc.

The food was good! We ordered chicken mushroom dumplings but the staff misheard and gave us pork cabbage dumplings instead     The dumplings were quite dry, but I would like to come back again to try the chicken mushroom ones next time. I also had beef tripe soup which turned out to be clear bouillon with beef organs (very yummy!  ) The service and atmosphere were not bad, but the place was very crowded. Also: be aware that it is customary to share your table with other people here, so keep that in mind when you come here to eat. Wheelchair accessibility: Would not recommend it because its very crowded.

Indeed one of the great places to enjoy affordable food. Im here at weekday lunch time around 1230pm, not as crowded but tables were filled quickly. Order taking is easy, the menu is straight forward. Tried their noodles with peanut sauce, 6 piece pork and chives dumplings, 6 piece fish ball soup. All for just $9, taste delicious. Noodles texture was just nice, peanut sauce added a great touch, paired it with chilis, heavenly awesome. Dumplings are unbeatable, food preparation is fast. Do drop by  if you around Chinatown.

If you have not tried Fukienese snacks, definitely do not miss out on this one. I have been to this place on multiple occasions, and I still keep going back. From time to time, I bring people there. The pork and cabbage dumpling are awesome, and the pork ball soup is Fukkienese classic. If you feeling adventurous, try the beef with starch soup, its not going to be ordinary dish, but you will certainly not regret. The place is packed with people, and you most likely will be sharing table with others. But, there are not many places in NYC where you can fill yourself up with $10 or under.
Cheap and Delicious! I spent $7 on a meal and Im full!

Heard about this place from an Instagram food blogger, so wanted to give it a try. It has all the hustle and bustle of a place in Hong Kong or China, a little hard to figure out the ordering or where to sit. But, have faith. It isnt hard! The menu is focused on dumplings, noodles and soups. As many have commented the peanut noodles are very good. Add some chili oil for more punch and depth. The pork and chive dumplings were truly excellent. Velvety exterior and hearty but not dense interior. Again, add the chili oil. We also ordered the vegetable dumplings which were packed with crunchy and fresh veggies. The stand out...fish bone soup. The lady who took my order wasnt sure if I ordered correctly, but I stuck to my guns and zero regrets. A lite broth, and big hunks of fish bones, glutenous, chewy and just damned delicious!

Cant beat the price and I didnt have to wait long even though there were several people waiting on the line while we waited for our order. The boiled dumplings were delicious and the spicy oil sauce was a good compliment adding some deep flavoring to each bite.

Great place with delicious food and very affordable pricing. Will be going here regularly. Some of the best dumplings in nyc!
As others have noted the pork & chive dumplings and peanut butter noodles are very good. However the hot and sour soup was very bland. NOTE: CASH ONLY!

Absolutely loved this! Very much reminded me of my Qingdao days abroad. The $3 peanut noodles, no frills, fabulous, and cannot beat the price! Their pork buns and some soups also piqued my interest. I will be returning to discover the wonders that remain unknown to me!
Did not disappoint.  No frills place, fast service and authentic food
The porc and cabage dumpling is ok, but the porc and chives dumplings are seriously delicious (with the chili oil)!
The dumplings are fantastic!! Its a small place,  so dont be bashful on asking a stranger to share their table. Definitely worth the walk to get here!!
Very great foooood !!!!!! I love them

First of all the prices here are very difficult to beat. $10 for 2 plates of noodles and dumplings. This is one of the best value for money places to eat at in NYC. They re quick service but because of everything that makes them great, they are very popular so you might have to wait a bit to dine in.
Delicious food for very reasonable price. Despite the quality of the food, the service is also top notch! Would recommend

Anyone who has given this spot less than 5 stars is either: A) a hater B) allergic to peanuts C) turned off by lines (though it moves quicker than youd think) Because this place is FANTASTIC! Their wheat noodles with peanut butter sauce are a must get. Delicious, creamy, and probably best $3 you can spend in the whole city. I cannot recommend it enough!
A true Chinatown institution. Great food, and the value is off the charts! Amazing
Its not very clean, but the food is amazing!
detailed_reviews.review_translated_text: No es muy limpio, pero la comida es increible!

detailed_reviews.review_text: Best pork buns Ive had in my life
Lovely lovely cheap and flavorful dumplings. I want to try the noodles with the peanut sauce one of these days. Cash only, so be ready.
Love it!

Located in Chinatown, this place is regarded as one of the best in the area for Chinese food. I wanted to try their dumplings and ordered chicken and mushroom dumplings along with veg soup. The dumplings were piping hot and were filling, the chicken in it was properly cooked and the minced mushroom didnt make me realize that they had added it in the mixture. Top it up with a bit of hot sauce and chilli oil, it tasted good. The soup was amazing too! I have always liked the soup at Asian restaurants, its always good to have them. The noodles were really soft and the veggies in it were boiled well. The broth was  well.. you know adjust according to our taste by adding the spice and it turned out to be good! Overall it felt good. Its a cash only place and not much of an ambiance. The service was pretty good, the servers were taking the orders till they shut the restaurant whereas they also let the patrons patiently have their food.

This place was sooooo good. I love that it s super cheap, but the food is still delicious. We got a variety of dishes, spent about $11 each, and were super full after eating. It can be difficult to find seating, so you have to watch over tables like a hawk, and you may have to sit with strangers. But it s so worth it. I give all the dishes we ate 10/10 except for the pickled vegetable noodles. They didn t have much flavor but weren t bad.

Cash only. Got the recommended pork/chive dumplings and the wheat noodles with peanut sauce for a total of $8 and it was great. It was enough to share between 2 people, but I ate almost all of it myself. The food came incredibly fast. The employees are nice and hard working. The place was crowded on a Wednesday evening but people are happy to share tables. The atmosphere is what you would expect in Chinatown--lots of people squeezing into the space for good food at a great price. Make sure you have some time to walk off the meal afterwards.
Delicious dumplings for an amazing price. Quick service, and eve peanut noodles are amazing too.
Excellent place, the food is very good and at a very good price, the service is also very good
detailed_reviews.review_translated_text: Excelente lugar, la comida es muy buena y a muy buen precio, la atencion tambien es muy buena

detailed_reviews.review_text: Pretty good. Good price decent food
The dumplings are to die for! The chili sauce has perfect flavor and goes very well with everything!
Traditional experience and food! We ordered the pork & chive dumplings + pork buns. So cheap & delicious !
Food was great and very cheap. Service is quick and responsive Food : 5/5
Unreal quality and quantity of food for the price. One of the best spots in Chinatown for dumplings, I would recommend the chicken and chive
They have some solid dumpling that you can t go wrong and it s cheap and taste good.
Best peanut noodles I ve tasted and very price friendly. It gets very packed around lunch time so try to go before the rush crowd. It s also a cash only place so make sure to have cash.
One of the last actually cheap eats left in the city. Cant go wrong with 3 dollar noodles
Pork and Chive Dumplings - Amazing Soups (wonton and hot and sour) - OK Super cheap! Noodles are popular, but I didn t get them. They look like a huge portion. Easily good for 3 people.
THE best takeaway frozen dumplings! Excellent quality...highly enjoyable!  Regular stop!
Peanut noodles are amazing!
Delicious and cheap dumplings. The peanut butter noodles are to die for!

This place needs a C rating from the NYC health department. The food for the price is great. Was a big fan of the steamed pork buns and wonton soup. However last time I went there I saw a kitchen staff member sneeze into her hand, not wash it and then took the steamed pork buns with the same hand and package it for me. I asked for a refund right away.
peanut noodle + dumplings + chrysanthemum tea combo stays undefeated
Loved it so much
Same great taste, year after year. My favorite dumplings in the city. Around the corner from their old location. Love the owners!

Was cash only and tax inclusive when I went. The dumpling fillings are so aromatic. Pork and chives was a hit! I stuffed myself for exactly $6. Would recommend a small order of dumplings and some noodles. Service was quick, sitting can be limited, but folks are down for sharing tables cafeteria style.
Dumpling heaven - get the pork and chive dumplings and peanut wheat noodles. remember CASH ONLY! Recommended dishes
Great simple food at a very cheap price. A great place to go for something quick and easy. Made relatively popular by YouTubers. The peanut noodles and the pork and chive dumplings are my go to

Cheap, fast, and tasty. This spot is a great stop off for a day in Chinatown. The chicken and chive dumplings were soooo addicting, and I also loved the beef soup. Just be prepared for limited seating.
Not good and small variety
Super cheap, super fast - delicious dumplings. Can t complain! Get them to go.
Delicious (and extremely affordable) food from across Chinas Fujian province and beyond!

i wouldn t come back because the food overall do not taste good / are not healthy. the pork buns are very dry inside and have very thic dough on the outside. the veggie dumplings were undercooked; i can still taste the dough. the fish bone soup was again a lot of dough and not a lot of fish, and a lot of MSG. the wontons were good; it might be the only thing i think it s worth getting. lastly the peanut butter noodles were good but it s just carbs. but all this said, you can t beat this price. it s just not something i personally would like to eat.

Cost-effectiveness itself! It was a decent meal for two women for $6 at scary New York prices. The inside of the store is self-service, except for ordering, and its not clean, but its good value for money. The dumplings were delicious and those peanut butter noodles were really amazing. Recommended!

My go to spot in Chinatown for cheap eats. This place is CASH ONLY so make sure to come prepared, otherwise there is an ATM outside. Strongly recommend the Pork and Chive Dumplings and the Peanut Noodles (dont get the think noodles). I would come with a friend and have one look for seating (first come first serve) while the other orders the food. You can have a full and filling meal here for less than $10, making it one of the cheapest places in NYC!
Smelly smelly food will make you a smelly smelly person

the rumors are true , run to this place   no frills , straight business for food. $3 noodles , $4.50 dumplings that are all fresh everytime. cash only. dont come here for no aesthetics this is pure food, and it should stay that way nice park next to it to hoop n chill too

Space is a little small for the crowd it attracts, but it was cozy and inviting on the rainy day we went. Peanut noodles and veggie dumplings were delicious; $3 and $5, respectively cant be beat! Service was quick and the portions were generous, easily shareable between two people. Will be back for my noodle and dumpling fix.
Favorite place for peanut noodles, just thinking about them makes me crave them. It can get really busy here, seating may not always be seating available so keep that in mind!

ig: @laura.eatsnyc Tried their pork and chicken dumplings - a steal at $4.50 for 10 pieces   Plus, their wheat noodles with peanut butter sauce? Incredibly addictive!   The beef tripe and thin rice noodle soup - not my fav, you can skip that one! Next time, I m diving into their fish ball soup - heard it s a must-try   Be ready for a line, though. Takeaway s the way to go!

When I ordered food at the front desk, I asked for Shaxian flat pork. They didn t say they didn t have it. They ordered local flat pork for me. I didn t know until the takeaway arrived home. Being hungry for a long time really affected my mood

The noodles!!! Nicest staff too!!
This place is fantastic.
Great food for just a few dollars. Go here with friends before going to drinks.
Fuzhou food is unrivaled
detailed_reviews.review_translated_text: Food

detailed_reviews.review_text: Fast service. Food was good. Im personally not a huge fan of peanut+noodles. But definately worth checking out! Pork buns were nice and filling. Must try with the chili sauces available :)

This was my first time in China Town NYC. I went here with the family and it was great experience. It s a small restaurant (if that s what u want to call it) but it s more like a carry out to me. The wait time was kind of long and it was crowded when we got there. It s a good atmosphere there and even though it s a tight seating area, everyone is respectful for one another and the food is awesome. The prices are reasonable, the food is great and we enjoyed our lunch there.

Quick and friendly service. Was greeted by the cashier with a warm smile. There was a bit of a line up to order but that just proved how great this restaurant was. If you re looking for cheap eats in NYC, this is your place. Spent $11 on 3 items. We got chicken and chive dumplings, peanut noodles, and spicy and sour soup. Would definitely return when we re back in NYC!
Good cheap Chinese food

Ordered dumplings and peanut noodles. We were so looking forward to the rice noodles in peanut sauce, but got the wrong thing, and the wrong thing unfortunately wasn t very good.. might be back to try what we originally ordered. Service : 2/5
Very inexpensive. Order at counter. Fight for table authentic Chinese food. Dumplings and soups seem to be the specialty

Great for exactly what you pay for! Cheap affordable food with quick service. The line ups may look daunting but the line up really goes by fast here. The peanut noodles and the dumplings are the most popular food items here. The peanut noodles were alright, not my favourite but filling. The dumplings were good, probably the cheapest dumplings I ve had while I was visiting NYC. It s worth the stop by if you re already visiting Chinatown.
ONLY CASH!!! $8 for a lot of noodles and 8 veggie dumplings!!! Super super good! Ill be back Food : 5/5
Cheap and tasty food. Between this, king dumplings, and taste restaurant, i cannot tell which is best
Nice spot. Cheap Chinatown place with a decent food. Cash only!

Seriously best boiled pork/chive dumplings ever. They dont do fried dumplings there. 6 for $3 (10 for $4.50 I think). Delicious and filling. Get a bag of frozen ones and make them at home! Love this place and this new location!!! The peanut noodles are delicious but need to eat them while hot!

A great place to go to if you want a cheaper meal that will keep you going for the rest of the day, but the flavors were bland to me. The soup in one of the noodle soup dishes I ordered was like chicken broth, and their peanut noodles seemed mushy. The only thing Id reorder are the pork/chive dumplings.

amazing place! Delicious and fun food in Ramat Cheap at a level you cant find in the United States at all!! I recommend the noodles in peanut sauce like everyone else and we also took a soup with wontons it was a favorite we tasted better, and we took gyoza with chicken and cabbage and pork and chives amazing!!!!

Amazing value for money!! The portions are more than fair and the food is delicious. Also, the dishes are ready in less than 10 minutes. We highly recommended this place. Important: they only accept CASH.
Delicious and affordable Shui Jiao. Place is crowded and you need to find seating yourself. Friendly service at the cashier and food is ready fast. I hope they never close!!
Pork and chive dumplings are great.
This place is always busy and for good reason! Worker at the front is very nice. Good cheap eats, great spot for a quick lunch if you re in the area
Excellent quality and cheap prices. Make sure to also get the frozen dumplings and other frozen items as well! $12 for 50 frozen dumplings!
Everything is authentic and delicious! Worth every penny!

We ordered chicken and mushroom dumplings and got some kind of weird beef looking thing. The item 1b seemed to be soy meat instead of beef and the taste after all is just bland. I m really sad because it looked good on videos.
Food was nice, but not the best, cheap,staff were nice,you get what you pay for
Good food, dirty and neglected place, very dirty bathroom, place for locals.
detailed_reviews.review_translated_text: Buena comida, el lugar sucio y descuidado , el bano muy sucio, sitio para locales.

detailed_reviews.review_text: You get what you pay for. I found a piece of hard, sharp plastic while eating their dumplings. Full on choking hazard that shouldnt be found in my food
Authentic Fujian foods with great prices that you can t find anywhere. The fish ball soup is a must have. Noticed everyone was having noodle with peanut, Will try next time.
This place is excellent in terms of value for price, as such there is always a line and I have not seen much seats, and being cash, they dont take cards!
Cash only. Unless you have your physical debit card, the ATM outside doesn t have tap to withdraw either. Waited in line to not be able to eat. Food looked good though.

Small hole in a wall shop, doesn t look like much and shop is cash only! We ordered the $3 peanut noodle that everyone raves about and the pork & chive dumplings. The peanut noodles were ok, nothing too special simple and filling. But the dumplings, those were amazing and the best part!! Would definitely come back again for the dumplings, the filling was nice and juicy. Use the dark sauce, it s a perfect combination. Portion size was very giving and food came quickly. There s a self-serve table with chopsticks/cutlery with soy sauce and vinegar.
Ordered the pork and chive dumplings and peanut oil noodles. Really delicious. Super cheap as well. They accept cash only and was there just after 10am

Came with a friend, we had the peanut butter noodles, pork Dumplings soup and pork & chive dumplings. It was aaall  delicious. Between those items +2 sodas and 1 water was $13. The place doesnt look that good but you for sure can let it go with the food taste and price
Tasty, plenty, affordable!

This place is a great Chinese restaurant!    Shu Jiao Fu Zhou serves a wonderful selection of delicious   authentic dishes   - definitely try their Thick Rice   Noodles   with Peanut   Sauce! Their prices   are very affordable and the portion size is great! This place has plenty of indoor seating    but you can also take your order to-go!   Staff    is friendly and professional and the service is quick.   I wish I knew about this place earlier!
Dumplings 10/10, the best Ive ever eaten. Pasta with peanut sauce 6/10 - a must try, but thats all. The smile of the lady who sells it 12/10. Prices ridiculously low.
detailed_reviews.review_translated_text: Pierogi 10/10, najlepsze jakie jad em. Makaron z sosem orzechowym 6/10 - trzeba sprobowa , ale to wszystko. U miech pani, ktora to sprzedaje 12/10. Ceny  miesznie niskie.

detailed_reviews.review_text: They got my friend throwing up all night. This place is nasty.
Cheap affordable food that tastes amazing. Get the tripe if you like tripe.
The dumplings got me throwing up all night this place is nasty
The peanut noodles are so good and addictive. I ve been dreaming about them since I last had them. And everything s super cheap too!

Best Pork and Chive dumplings in Chinatown. Fantastic noodles with peanut sauce. I m a bit obsessed with this place    I like a more delicate shell and these guys deliver a light translucent shell that is fantastic. The filling is consistently excellent. Compared to King Dumplings and another local place these guys make by far the best filling and the best shell. I highly recommend boiled over fried. The chicken mushroom dumplings are also outstanding. They make hot and sour soup in a different style. Probably because of the region but theirs has pickles in it which I haven t seen before. Don t come here for the atmosphere because there isn t any - strictly no frills but lightning quick service and amazing food more than make up for that.
a gem

This place is perfectly unassuming with a great selection of flavorful favorites and it s so inexpensive! We had 6 pieces each of pork and chive dumplings, chicken and mushroom dumplings, pork buns, an order of their famous peanut butter noodles (which go great topped with their chili crunch), and two drinks for only $17. Absolutely delicious!
The food was great, the service was fast and cheap.

I saw this place on tiktok and decided to go on my visit to New York. I never tried peanut noodles before and must say that for the price they worth it so much! I love chinatown so much! The Food is great, is cheap and you really get to felt the culture. The dumplings were not that amazing as everyone was saying in the reviews but for sure they are great.
Awesome!
One of the best steam dumplings and peanut butter noodles restaurant in Manhattan Chinatown NYC
This place was absolutely horrible, idk why you would eat here with all the Asian food around you.
Very tasty
The hype is justified. The food is authentic and delicious. The peanut butter noodles is outstanding and the pork and chive dumplings are amazing. A definite must.
I love   this place its my go to when Im in Chinatown I didnt get a chance to try everything because Im so hooked on the chicken chives dumplings and peanut noodles but its a  up for me
super tasty and super affordable and super nice!!!!

If you love Chinese food and happen to be in NYC do not miss out on this place. My go to are their peanut noodles and pork and chive (soooo juicy!!) dumplings and the portions are huge at an unbeatable price point. Friendly staff as well!
We are here visiting from the UK.  Very good food.

My comfort food. If you re a big fan of peanuts, then this restaurant is a must-visit on your list. But if you re allergic to peanuts, yo o.O, sorry for your loss lol. The restaurant used to occupy a small corner space on a quiet block of Eldridge Street, but after the pandemic, the owners have relocated to a bigger space at 295 Grand Street. When you visit, here s what you need to do: get in line and when it s your turn, order up number 4 and 5! Trust me, these dishes are my go-to every time I visit and they never disappoint. And one last thing. It s super cheap

This unassuming and ridiculously cheap place in NY is going to be your favorite as soon as you try it, trust me! The go to s include: - dumplings - authentic, slightly sweet, delicious - peanut noodles - the fantastic simple dish so full of flavor it s unbelievable And the best part is You can get both and a drink and still pay under $10!
Awesome dumplings and noodle rice.
$12 for 50 delicious frozen dumplings? It s a bargain, an easy staple everyday meal.

For no frizzles cheap eats in Chinatown, this is the spot. My total was 9 dollars for 6 dumplings, noodles, and soup. The noodles were salty and nutty but the sauce was not overly thick to have an overpowering peanut taste. The dumplings are soft and stuff with a good ratio. The soup is delicious with depth of flavor. Definitely worth a visit if your on a tight budget.
Over rated!

Considering not posting this just to gatekeep this place. The noodles and dumplings are amazing and at an unbeatable price. I ve already come back twice this week- probably the best $3 you can spend in nyc. Vegetarian options: they now have veggie dumplings which is a major plus
Great food and prices
Quick eat. Good Fuzhou food (dumplings are awesome). Very affordable.

Best value food we found in NYC. Delicious dumplings and noodles, served fresh by friendly staff at crazy prices. Small old school eating area so grab your food to go and watch the basketball/handball games in the park nearby. Cash only.
This place is amazing. Delicious food and low prices. Cash only so don t forget cash
real basic, real tasty, and really cheap. the real deal.
It s great for takeout or a quick eat. Their wheat peanut sauce noodles are wonderful! Food
Must come when in Chinatown. One of the best value for cost ratios in the city. Favorite items: pork & chive dumplings, peanut noodles, frozen dumplings
Best dumpling I ve ever eaten! Especially the chilli oil is amazing with it
The food was decent, but the dine-in experience was not that great.

Cheap and delicious. Edit: They have added steamed pork buns and vegetable dumplings to the menu recently. Both are delicious. I purchased 100 frozen pork dumplings for a friend in the suburbs and she said it was her favorite birthday present by far! Vegetarian options: Peanut butter noodles
peanut noodles and dumplings are a must get. however the place has a problem with beggars in the front, just ignore them and go in, order, pay, eat then leave.
We had peanut butter noodle, dumpling and fish ball soup. All are Delicious and very good value. Definitely recommend it.
I always get the same two dishes; wheat noodles with peanut sauce and pork and chive dumplings.  Been going there for half a dozen years and it s always tasty!!
Came on a Sunday morning around 10 AM and it wasn t busy. You know it s legit when they re screaming fuzhounese in the back, feels like home : )
Good food, crowded Vegetarian options: No meat options Kid-friendliness: Family olace
Awesome cheap eats to be found at this dumpling shop! All the items are steamed or boiled, and they ve super savory and hearty. Doing the local community a true service!
Cheap & tasty eats. Dumplings highly recommended! It s a cash only place
Incredibly cheap, incredibly good dumplings and noodles
Did not dine in ordered to take away but the wait for theb order was  not long at all. The food was inexpensive and tasted great.
all the food is so affordable and its made right when you order it and it comes out pretty quick too

This place was packed! They do have indoor seating if I personally recommend grab and go. The food was good for the price, which is partially why we went so no complaints. We only waited about 10 minutes or less for our food. Would definitely return or recommend for in general and for someone in a budget forsure! They is to ask for and extra sauce if possible.

This is the epitome of Chinatown cheap eats. Somewhat limited menu but you can t go wrong with any selection. Everything your order comes out super fast. They called out by number and it s all self-serve. I trekked in from Queens in the pouring rain due to many youtube videos stating this is one of the must have, its no lie. The hour long drive was well worth it. Everything I had came out to only $10, now if that s not a bargain in this day and age then I don t know what is. Too bad I am on a Chinatown food crawl or else I would devour more on this menu. Just wish this restaurant is a bit cleaner.
Incredible food for prices you cant beat. The peanut noodles (#5) and the wonton soup (#7) are only $6 total. Its a classic/traditional combination that I highly recommend trying together.
Wasnt particularly crazy about the soup or dumplings they were okay. This place is relatively inexpensive
Great prices and excellent food range! Worth it

I m so happy to see such a classic NYC cheap eats place still thriving! The food here is excellent and the prices have managed to stay very low. The $4.50 dumplings were some of the best cheap ones I ve had. They had a think skin and a really juicy, flavorful filling. The pork s buns are good but there are better ones. The peanut noodles are really something special and it s such a unique taste that for only $3 you have to get it at least once, if not more, in your lifetime. The staff is always very nice and I ve never had an issue here.
Excellent food and cheap ...tried chicken and chive momos.
cheap, delicious, easy. food came out hot and quickly   would come again
Great tasting food and a great price!

Peanut Wheat Noodles - Noodles were al dente with a slight chew and are a wider, which by itself feel really good in your mouth and give a nostalgic, comforting feeling. The wide noodles grab onto the peanut sauce very well and tastes super aromatic and rich of peanuts, with a little bit of soy sauce and oil to it. Extremely addicting, beware. Pork and Chive Dumplings - Pretty good wrapping and filling proportions, and filling itself tasted very good. Porky umami along with a fresh chives taste, Fish Balls - Smooth yet bouncy fish balls wrapped around a juicy pork filling, and is a wonderful combination of both land and seafood umami flavours together in one bite. Watch out as I burned my mouth because I was too excited. The broth was pretty bland though. Check out @bredgyeats for food pictures!
This place was heavenly. The peanut noods were delectable
Vegetarian options: The peanut noodles is vegetarian Food
detailed_reviews.review_translated_text: Food

detailed_reviews.review_text: Fast, cheap, and flavorful food. Keep this gem the way it is, don t bother anyone. Order that food and move on with your life. Get the peanut wheat noodles and a 10pc pork & chive dumpling. Don t forget to leave a tip. Ask for extra chili oil, you ll thank me later. One of the best spots.
It was just perfect! Extremely good dumplings (tried them all, every option is the right one to choose), good price, nice staff. Would come back any time. Thank you!
Amazing

5 star value in NYC. We got a ridiculous amount of food for only $17 (see photo). Everything was surprisingly good, but will probably skip the wonton soup next time. Will definitely come back! Side note, don t give money to the beggars if they come into the store asking for $ or food.
Best dumps in Manhattan Chinatown.
Incredible restaurant in the heart of Chinatown, we got it for barely $8 each.
detailed_reviews.review_translated_text: Incroyable restaurant en plein c ur de Chinatown, nous en avons eu pour a peine 8$ chacun.

detailed_reviews.review_text: It is still delicious and very cheap in price and very delicious!
detailed_reviews.review_translated_text: Sigue siendo deliciosa y muy barata en precio y muy rico!

detailed_reviews.review_text: no frills, fast paced cheap and delicious food! i had the wheat peanut noodles and the pork chive dumplings, all fantastic. Food

Affordable, and quick food. Their pork and chive dumplings are really yummy for the price - the noodles are a bit lacking in flavor though. Its a bit busy with it being somewhat viral right now - but the line moves quick. Its just tough to find a seat

This place has been here forever. I always enjoy coming. However I feel as though since it went viral, the food and service is no longer the same. The place has not yet gotten used to the influx of tourists and people coming to get the cheap eats. Ordered the pork buns, peanut noodles, chicken and mushroom dumplings, and pork and chive dumplings. The good: flavors were good and the prices are still amazing. $4.50 for 10 dumplings, $3 for noodles, and $5 for the buns. Cost us $17 total to feed 5 people the best we had today was their pork bun and pork and chive dumplings. The bad: very slow service due to how many people were in there, however, the place seemed very disorganized because they call you by number. There were people receiving food within 5 mins, whereas we waited for 20-25 mins. The peanut noodles had very little flavor, definitely disappointing. The chicken and mushroom noodles also were not very tasty.
I was informed about this place at my job. For lunch my supervisor and I would get on the train from midtown and get lunch. Very reasonable and food gives you a different kind of vibe.
Instant my favourite place. Incredible food for an incredible price. I love this place!!!

I saw a post about this place somewhere on social media and added it to my bucket list.  Shut Jiao Fu Zhou is a small restaurant located in China town. It was very hot and crowded there, no available  tables and long line from the door.  My first impression was just to walk away, but I decided to give  it a try. The line moved pretty fast, and eventually we were able to secure a table.  We ordered soup,  dumplings to share and noodles.The food  was very delicious for a great price. I would highly recommend this place and definitely would come back. Thank you

Cheap and delicious eats! Ordered the peanut noodles and the pork&chives dumplings. Total was 8 dollars, and it was a filling meal. Both were quite good, but the dumplings in particular stood out to me, would recommend

The thick noodles in peanut butter sauce was very bland I took two bites and had to hold it to my nose to make sure it was actually peanut butter in it. What was was shown on social media didn t look anything like what I was given and the portion is very small. Same size they give you a small soup in. It was only 3 buck but then again it was only noodles as well

The meat is old and spoiled ..... dont go here. The place is so dirty . The food is like frozen for so many years . Its cheap because they give you rotten spoil meat . You will sit in the bathroom or end up in the hospital .
The best pork dumplings I ve ever had!
The food is always great . Cash only but so worth it . The hardest part is finding somewhere to sit lol.
Chicken & Chives vibes .  Fresh & delicious!  Those wheat peanut noodles hit different . IYKYK
Good Chinatown cheap eats. Always busy. Pretty fast line. Food okay but cheap as dirt.

It can get a little chaotic in this place, but there s no denying it s incredible value. It definitely ranks very high in this city in terms of tasty and cheap meals. Dumplings and their Fujian style peanut butter noodles are both great. Peanut butter noodles were a lunch favorite of mine when I lived in Shanghai and these were pretty decent.
This place is so yummy.  The peanut noodles and dumplings were amazing the steamed buns were the best.
Peanut noodles are soooo good delicate and super tasty, pork and Chive dumplings my favorite very juicy
Slightly above mid

10/10 recommend! This place is busy for a reason, and grab a seat while you can because it won t be empty for long! The prices are PHENOMENAL! Not incredibly clean, and water is $1 (they don t offer tap), but the price and food is great!
First time but definitely not last time! 3 dollars per menu item. Cant beat that!

My all-time favorite Chinese eatery in Manhattan. I discovered this place in 2015 when it was still in its old location and was blown away by the taste and value of its food! Over the past eight years, every time I visit NYC, this is the place I must stop by for at least one time. Every friend or family member that I brought here is also impressed by the place and agrees that this is an one-of-kind authentic eatery.
$3 peanut noodles. Amazing price, but not very flavorful.
Bare bones dining room but can you really complain when theres $3 noodle plates and $5 sour vegetable soup? Right answers only. Lots of flavor for not a lot of money and the kitchen is FAST.

Amazing dumplings, get there early for fresh dumpling and yummy thin noodles with chicken or beef stock. Must visit if you are in the China town of NY, which is very authentic Chinese food. Little crowded, I would suggest you get a takeaway!!

Saw this place on TikTok, and I had to try it!!!!! Dumplings were SO good, and the fact that theyre made by hand is so cool! I definitely ordered way too many cause they filled me up! They were nice and soft, and the filling was SO good! I didnt really care for the soup, though! It just didnt have any flavor, and the protein was too chewy, I ended up throwing it all away. But for the prices, this is a nice quick eat that you cant pass up! I wish the Sriracha they had on the tables was the actual sauce, but instead, its some house made sauce. Its too watery, and the flavor is WAY off!
Fill your stomach for $6? Yup. Great prices, casual walk-in vibe, and food is good for the price
They have vegetarian dumplings now :)

The BEST dumplings i ve ever had in my life. I got the pork and chive. Add the soy sauce and chili oil on top and it s life changing. Let s not forget the fact that it s only $4.50 for 10 dumplings?!! I d eat here everyday if I lived in NY
Fast and good food. Which all the tiktokers would go away but doesnt change that this place is good

What more could you ask for than tasty, inexpensive dumplings? You can get a quick bite for very little money  and be on your way. The line can get a little long during the more popular times of day but overall its pretty quick. They also have a community seating atmosphere so you can usually sit down and eat if youre comfortable rubbing elbows with your fellow New Yorkers.

Fav noodle spot, the noodles and the peanut flavor was just the right amount + dumplings. I stopped here and it was busy but the line moves super fast and I got my order surprisingly quick. Definitely must visit when you re in Chinatown

Good food. Great if you work in the area and need some quick cheap eats during break. Takes like 10 minutes to get your food. Seating can be an issue though. Vegetarian options: No Parking: Its the city. Parking is hard to come by. Kid-friendliness: No Wheelchair accessibility: No steps in the place but so small you might not fit in a chair when packed.
They provide very delicious food with very decent price. I will definitely come back again.
Extremely affordable, the authentic Chinatown experience
The food is really good, and very inexpensive, which makes it unbeatable value for money! The only downside is that the number of places to eat inside is quite limited.
detailed_reviews.review_translated_text: La nourriture est vraiment bonne, et tres peu chere ce qui fait un rapport qualite prix imbattable! Seul bemol, le nombre de place pour manger a l interieur est assez limite.

detailed_reviews.review_text: A place I must visit every time I go to New York. This is a cost-effective restaurant where you can eat a large plate of their signature peanut noodles and water dumplings for just $7.50! The dumplings are really delicious, so be sure to try them! Instead, they only accept cash, so be prepared in advance.

This place is my favorite place to eat , it s so affordable , you can eat good for less than $10 , the chili oil is good the peanut butter noodles are great and so is the pork buns and dumplings and also soups I recommend Coming here , it s a bit crowded sometimes because tourist do come and it s cash only
Make sure you order the correct peanut noodle.  One is flat the other is spaghetti like
Best place ever, the fish balls, the vibes, the prices, the peanut noodles WOW
Hunk of plastic inside dumplings. They also have a problem with folks begging inside the establishment.
Cheap, tasty, authentic
This place  is why I m paying NYC rent Got a bag of 50 frozen dumplings for $12. They take 5 min to cook and taste like heaven.

Got 6 pork + chive and 6 chicken + mushroom dumplings for a grand total of $6. The price is UNREAL and the dumplings were SO good - thin wrapper with some bite, juicy filling. I could tell they cooked them fresh. My family s dumplings will always be my favorite but if I can t have those, I ll be coming here. Just fyi - it s cash only.
Very cheap, fast, no frills dumplings available in 4 options.  We ordered 30 dumplings, small fish ball soup, and a peanut noodle all for $19.50.  Cash only.

It got tiktok famous, but is it really worth the hype and the trip? Yes. Without considering the price, the dumplings and noodles are quite good. The chili vinegar for the dumplings is tangy and light, to balance the meatiness of the filling. The noodles are soft, but still springy, and are savory from the use of peanut butter (or oil?). In the context of the price, the food outperforms for the money, and will also fill you up to boot.
Two of us ate for 7,5$ and it was amazing!! Must see Must eat.

Dumplings were great--chewy and flavourful. Noodles were hit and miss. Wheat noodles were al dente but rice noodles, in my opinion, too soggy. But good value. When busy seating is short. You can also order out or get frozen dumplings to cook.

If you want to eat quickly, cheaply and well, come eat at this place. The atmosphere, the food, the staff, everything is good. If I can recommend a dish, take the rice noodles with peanut sauce. For $3 per dish on average you wont be disappointed.
Great fresh food for cheap. Large portions !
My favorite restaurant while visiting in NYC. I want to live upstairs and eat here everyday ! Food is extremely cheap and delicious
Secret spot that I go to whenever I have cash and am in the LES. Call ahead and order by the # corresponding to the menu item for expedited service
Food slaps and prices are crazy cheap.
The food is great and cheap! One can always rely on Chinatown for cheap good eats. Ignore their service tho, can be annoying
Food is ok but price is right.

Just wow, so much flavor. The wheat noodles with peanut butter sauce were incredible. Also the steamed pork buns and wonton soup. So cheap, only spent $11 and food was delicious and so filling. Highly recommend!!
20years ago, my first time here with my dad, he told me this owner was well known for making these food in our hometown.

Amazin dumplings. Some of the best Ive had. Great dumpings excellent and speedy service. Essentially zero wait time, deliciously authentic dumplings at very budget friendly pricing. Stuffing was very good, not too dense but filled in nicely. Dumpling skin was nice and soft.
AMAZING DUMPLINGS, YOU WONT BE DISAPPOINTED. We tried the pork and chive dumplings and they were simply delicious and only $4.50 for 10 dumplings!!
Best dumplings Ive ever had in my life, easily. A must go hole in the wall spot if youre in the area

Bought a huge bag of 50 heavy dumps yesterday for 12$ they were so unbelievably good and especially for the price! Also bought a big can of homemade soya can, which is so incredibly good! Recommended place!
detailed_reviews.review_translated_text: Kobte en kaempe pose med 50 tunge dumpnings i gar til 12$ de var sa ufatteligt gode og isaer til prisen! Kobte ogsa en stor dunk hjemmelavede soya dunk, som er sa utroligt go! Anbefalelsesvaerdigt sted!

detailed_reviews.review_text: Incredibly delicious food! The atmosphere is very busy and there is a lot to look at. We thought it was good that the waste was separated at the end.
detailed_reviews.review_translated_text: Unfassbar leckeres Essen! Die Atmosphare ist sehr trubelig und man hat viel zu schauen. Gut fanden wir, dass der Mull am Ende getrennt wird.

detailed_reviews.review_text: So hard to find such a homie taste in the US, although it is not exactly the same, it looks 90 percent closer and tastes 70 percent closer to the original ones. Must have a try
Absolutely amazing I love everything about the food here
Delicious dumplings, good pasta with peanut sauce and average soup. Nice service, quick service and very affordable prices.
detailed_reviews.review_translated_text: Pyszne pierogi, dobry makaron z sosem orzechowym i  rednia zupa. Mi a obs uga, szybkie podanie i bardzo przyst pne ceny.

detailed_reviews.review_text: wheat noodles with peanut butter sauce - nutty, as you would expect but other than that there s nothing to rave about. i added vinegar and some chili oil to mine which turned out nice. notes this is coming from someone who dislikes peanut forward dishes. at first, i ate it for courtesy as my friend shared it with me but i did find myself going back for more. overall, simple and satisfying.

Shu Jiao Fu Zhou is quick, efficient and delicious and I m just talking about the prices lol but I m all seriousness the $3 noodles in peanut sauce are GLORIOUS!!! [Throw in a splash of soy sauce to get the best flavor]
The noodles are soooo good and the frozen dumplings are delicious, plus everything is so cheap.
Really affordable prices Good food I ate at the place but I felt is not clean the tables are dirty no napkins . Is a fast food place. I had : pork chives dumplings and the peanut noodles
Yummy dumplings
Dumplings was ok but just ok. The tables were very dirty and the place itself is not comfortable
Go for the chive dumpling and make sure you order at least 10:)
Every time my wife and I come to NYC we stop here for breakfast. So delicious, good price, and fast service! We love the peanut noodles and the dumplings. It s definitely comfort food.
Honestly, the best dumplings I had in my life. Ridiculously tasty.
Amazing dumplings
cash only and bad attitude
Best dumplings ever. It crowded cause it s very cheap and tasty
Dumplings were awesome and at good prices!
Vegan peanut noodles. Cash only. Yes bathroom. No free water. Vegan china town
This is the only place I go to get lunch during work! Best dumpings in Chinatown for sure! Simply outstanding. Also love the what noodle, fish ball soup, and newly added pork buns.
I like the food here. I basically eat here every week at work, but what I met today makes me feel very disgusting . will never come back.
Cheap, portions are good, and the food is good. Not exceedingly jaw dropping but I can t complain! Food
You get what you pay for. Their Sriracha is some mysterious sauce that Im pretty sure gave me diarrhea  but overall their dumplings are still yummy.
So delicious! Got the pork and chive, chicken and chive, and chicken and mushroom dumplings. Also a side of beef tripe soup.
You couldnt get any cheaper than this. Cash only
really really cheap for nyc
Authentic Chinese street food in heart of Chinatown. This brought me back to the days I lived in China. Do not be put off by the tiny space! It s a fire meal at an unbeatable price.

I would rate this a 3.5 but will bump it up due to the very friendly and fast service. We ordered frozen dumplings to go (great flavor but you just never know what type of meat they actually put into these things), small wontons and the fat meatball wontons. The small wontons are somewhat similar to the authentic version youd get in southern China (Fuzhou, Xiamen, etc.) but its a bit too doughy. The fat meatball wontons on the other hand are absolute monstrocities and I would NOT recommend them. Essentially so dense that its hard to boil/cook them, theyre pretty nasty. Stick to the other commonly found Chinatown noodles/dumpling dishes here.
Keep in mind it s CASH ONLY! There is atm outside though. Dumplings, fish ball soup and peanut butter noodles were very good my kids loved it too. Good prices
Cozy, yummy, insanely affordable. Not much more you can ask for.
Food is decent and cheap

First of all, this place is super affordable and the service is friendly.  They dont serve alcohol typically, but had a single white claw that they sold me for $3, lol.  We tried the beef noodle soup, peanut noodles, and pork and chive dumplings.  The peanut noodles and dumplings were out of this world good!  The total for all that was $10:50 - its hard to beat that!
Their food is delicious And affordable, trust me Youre going to love it Food : 5/5
Local food.  Taste is average.  Low cost.

Absolutely a great place, stunning food. New on the menu are pork buns, amazing. Try the dumplings, pork ball soup, peanut butter noodles. You wont regret. The staff is friendly, efficient and nice. Place can be crowded, so sharing of tables is normal.
Amazingly delicious dumplings!

Great, fast, inexpensive food. Dumplings, noodles with peanut sauce and pork buns were all good! Come here for affordability and consistency, but dont expect any frills! The chili condiment available at the table put the dishes over the top
Good food. Self-service. Staff can speak English.
Best pork and chive dumplings. Ever.

I had the wrong expectations going into this spot - here s what you should know: people love it because it s cheap. I thought it would also have good food, but it s just cheap food. The dine in experience is poor as well: dirty tables, sauces running low, and a strange, stale smell in the air that isn t appetizing at all. Only thing I enjoyed eating was the chive and pork dumplings (we tried 7 different things, including a few noodle dishes, buns, soups). If you want a cheap meal, this is the spot for you!
Fj taste, quick service, hot soup. fishballs are juicy and peanut noodles are good. One bathroom.
If you re looking for a quick and affordable bite   this is the place; serving up noodles in peanut sauce and boiled dumplings.
I got the pork dumplings and it made me sick for a week. Really dont recommend this place.
Such a great place for delicious food at an affordable price!
Everything was disgusting, from the poor quality food to the disposable plastic plates and cutlries!
This gem has the best and the meatiest dumplings in Chinatown! You cant beat their prices & their speedy service either!
simply delicious dumplings and peanut noodles! I constantly crave them and wish I lived closer to come more often.
Can t turn down 3$ fish ball soup. One thing that is worth noting is that there are constantly weird people coming in, and I feel sorry that the ladies at the store had to deal with it.

Excellent noodles with peanut sauce, so addictive. I m not vegetarian but these are yummy! Frozen dumplings and buns are great for home cooked meals when you are short on time, fast service and friendly Vegetarian options: The wheat noodles in peanut sauce is awesome

Came here after seeing that this was the hidden gem. But it I sadly disagree. The only thing positive for me was the really cheap price. The three dishes were less than $10. The dumplings were the most tasty out of the three, but still mediocre. We also got more protein of a fly
Good food for a great price, especially liked the peanut noodles and porkball soup. Wheelchair accessibility: Super wheelchair accessibel, toilet included!

I was in the area and was craving dumplings when I found this place. Shu Jiao Fu Zhou is cash only, but its worth having cash for! I ordered wheat noodles, dumplings, and pork buns for just $11. The food is amazing and super low in price compared to other places. Highly Recommend!

These dumplings are great and especially for the price! (I think it was $12 for all the food we got). We got the chicken and the pork but I honestly couldn t tell the difference between the two. My kids loved the noodles in the peanut sauce. It wasn t the cleanest restaurant (had to wipe down the table ourselves and the floor was metal and sticky) so only knock for not giving 5 stars. But very tasty and delicious and fair price.
Food was cold and not that tasty. If you want really good cheap dumplings, you have to go to Super Taste. Much better. 2 stars because its cheap.
detailed_reviews.review_translated_text: Essen war kalt und nicht so lecker. Wer richtig gute gunstige Dumplings will, muss zu Super Taste gehen. Viel besser. 2 Sterne weil es billig ist.

detailed_reviews.review_text: Very cheap and good food. It smells delicious.
Dumplings were delicious and authentic! The fish ball soup was perfect for brunch following a night out. The restaurant itself is very casual.
The dumplings were amazing and the people were so nice!
A chef s kiss.
Great dumplings and soups. Kind of cafeteria vibe.
Would 100% recommend. Super yummy cheap food. It s a gem.

I was very surprised after visiting here, both in terms of portions, taste and price. Very large portions, very good taste, very short waiting time and very low prices. A nice alternative to other more expensive places. I recommend trying it

detailed_reviews.review_text: Best pork and chive dumplings in Chinatown!! But honestly everything here is amaaazing the wheaten noodles, fish ball soup .yummm. We come here once a week at least and it never gets old!

The quantities are enormous. We took ravioli by 10. We also had peanut noodles, the quantity was huge but it was a little lacking in taste. On the other hand, too many people there, we took takeaway. The prices are very attractive

detailed_reviews.review_text: Really tasty home cooked food at dirt cheap prices. Dumplings taste authentic and homemade. The peanut noodles were a bit lacking in sauce but also tasty. You d be hard pressed to find better value in nyc let alone Chinatown. Cash only!
Great Value - Frozen Dumplings are great to bring home and the peanut butter sauce noodles are awesome!
Super-busy simplistic canteen with delicious dim sums and noodle. Great place, will definitely come back!
Really quality food for awesome prices!
Great food, cheap prices, would highly recommend
It is a perfect place if you are in Chinatown and have a low budget. Its not the cleanest thing in the world but the food is great for the price. Cash only!
detailed_reviews.review_translated_text: Es un sitio perfecto si andas por Chinatown y tienes low budget. No es lo mas limpio del mundo pero la comida por el precio esta genial. Cash only!

detailed_reviews.review_text: The absolute best cheap dumplings & peanut butter noodles in Chinatown PERIOD
Best dumplings and wheat noodles ever,  I love them and go there a lot Wheelchair accessibility: There is room for wheelchairs
Dumplings. Thats all you need to know. I accidentally over-ordered and ended up eating 25 in one sitting. It was great, and cheap. I love this place

Five star! Taste - 5. Portion - 5. Price - 6 :) I tried there first time pork and chive dumplings and second time chicken and chive dumplings plus of course noodle with peanut butter. Two dishes for me was too much :) Even after good joint ;) And customer service is very friendly. Prices are amazing! What to expect more? Yummy peanut noodles for only 3$ , dumplings were also really good

Incredibly tasty dumplings and peanut noodles. Great price too

detailed_reviews.review_text: Incredible. Had to write a review as I m still sitting in the restaurant - INSANE prices, INSANE flavor! Come now!!!

Visiting NYC for the first time and saw a vlog about this place so we wanted to give it a try. Its definitely a must go. The price is right and the dumplings are amazing. We also tried the peanut butter noodles and my kids finished it before I could have a taste. The place was packed, but the wait wasnt long. We ordered to go but had a table open up so we dined in. Worth it as the chilli oil was also very good. I personally liked mixing it with the black sauce they had at the table too. Not sure what its called but it along with the chilli oil made the dumplings even more delicious. We thought we ordered enough to have leftovers to pack back to the hotel but before we knew it, it was all gone. If you got preteen to teenage kids and visiting NYC, give this place a try. Its in Chinatown too so theres tons more things to do and eat, well worth the trip.
Very good dumplings! The price is very fair! Ambiente was typical China town.
This place did not disappoint. Their famed peanut wheat noodles were delicious and the dumplings were amazing stuffed to the brim with filling!! Also its sooo affordable. 10 Stars
best restaurant in chinatown

Great spot for cheap and delicious noodles, soups and dumplings. The lady at the front was super nice and the food was tasty! A top notch nyc chinatown experience! We especially liked the pork and chives dumplings as well as the peanut noodles.
AMAZING. i literally dream abt this place whenever im not here.

Its a crazy crowded, crazy cheap eatery. Is the food here top shelf? No, they crank it in droves for hungry college aged kids. But honestly? Ive had dumplings all over the place and these ones werent bad at all. Fat, plump and flavoursome. The service is good, the people running it are actually nice, and its kinda fun in low key, crowded as hell jostling for a table sort of way.

Awesome value for asian food eats! As part of a second dinner, two of us ordered a large pork and chive dumplings ($4.50), a small fish ball soup ($3) and a wheat noodle with peanut butter sauce ($3). Dumplings and fish ball soup were good. I would avoid the wheat noodle and peanut sauce. Flavorless and overcooked. Cash only! They have some seating inside. Follow the adventure @shoyuthebest on IG!
Cheap, good, fast.
4.50 for 10 incredible pork dumplings. cant be beat
Been coming here for a while. Today there was a dead roach in my noodles. I want to come back because I love it, hope precautions are being taken.

Thanks to xiaomanyc for the recommendation - food is superb for the price - easily a <10$ lunch option here. Peanut noodles is delectable, and price for the amount is great. Inside is a typical Chinatown feel, some tables and seats, cashier is straight ahead upon entry, restroom is labelled wheelchair accessible. Friendly and professional staff. Very tasty. Quick order and served fast. Dumplings on point. Was here for breakfast.

I came based on the raving reviews. Fast service but food is bland and is on par with cafeteria food in China. If you need something fast, filling, and cheap, this is great. It is healthy food, but just bland and normal.

I love this place! It s one of few remaining food places from my childhood. Food is cheap and delicious!

All the food is delicious, cheap, and fast. The pork and chive dumplings are my favorite!

They have really tasty dumplings at unbeatable prices for the amazing quality and taste. I highly recommend stopping by to try their Pork and chives dumpling! I tried their pork & chives dumpling, their fish balls and their peanut butter wheat noodles. The fish balls missed the mark for me & if I add a little more flavor to the peanut butter noodles it would ve been great! It s a fast pace restaurant, which was busy and bustling with business when I stopped by today. Seeing food from my province enjoyed by people from different backgrounds is heartwarming. Their hot sauce is watered down btw. They have really good dumpling sauce which pairs the dumplings perfectly. There is paid parking right outside this business. Great spot. Get the pork and cabbage dumplings. Soup is good too. Some seats inside. Can also bring frozen dumplings home. Also had the soup which was solid too. Will be going back very soon. Thank you!!

A true representation of affordable and filling food in the area. I got the chicken and mushrooms, and chive dumplings. They were so hearty, but still soft to the touch and delicate. Highly recommend for anyone wanting to eat in Chinatown on a budget.
The dumplings were really delicious and flavorful. They also sell bags of frozen dumplings. We will definitely be back.
Very good place

Awesome spot
my boyfriend and I love to come here to eat something good and fast. Really nice place to come and visit here in China town

Left the place around 12 as it was getting crowded and my seat was needed. Had the noodles in peanut sauce, fishball soup and pork/chives dumplings. Noodles had a great texture which I really enjoyed even though Im not a big fan on such flat noodles. Peanut sauce had some good flavour to it but needed a little extra vinegar and chilli oil (which are readily available together with sriracha). Soup was just a plain soup with slight flavouring probably from the fishballs and abit of salt/msg. Fishballs were good but not fantastic. Got a nice bite to it and flavourful enough. Theyre a Fuzhou specialty with meat in it so when you bite into them, the meat juices spurts out which is pretty enjoyable. Best dish has got to be the dumplings. Really tasty and I just couldnt get enough of them. Skin was smooth and the meat filling was just delicious. Pretty much every table had some variations of dumplings on their table so that tells you all you need to know. All of that was only for $9. Cheap and delicious. Ill definitely be back very often.

Is this somewhere youd take a date to? No Is this where youd swing by for a great noodle dish and some fishballs for $6 total? Hell yes

Ill just come out and say it, this place is a gem! The from the peanut noodles to the tripe soup. The menu is excellent. However the crown jewel of this establishment is the Pork and Chive dumplings. In my humble opinion the dumplings are the best in Lower Manhattan!
So happy they expanded to new location. Picked up 6 bags of frozen dumplings for the family. Everybody is satisfied as usual

This place has the best hand made fish ball period! Their fish ball is unique in Fu Zhou style. Their dumplings are very good too and you can order frozen dumplings 50 pcs for $12. Their price is very cheap even after they have increased the price early this year. This place is definitely a  Cheap  eat place. However, this place is very dirty and environmentally unfriendly. They use plastic dishes and bowls even you re dining in at the restaurant. -1 star for dine in condition. They really need to do some deep cleaning for the whole restaurant. Quick tips: The seating is first come first server table grabs. You need to clean your own table before and after you re done. This place is DIRTY!
Dumplings were alright. There are better in the area
Delicious and affordable! Business is booming
One of the best frozen dumplings and noodles in New York City. I can t remember how many times I revisited here tbh.

Right when you walk in you can tell this place is authentic. Every time I come here there is a line and it s pretty obvious why. The food here and cheap and it s good. Make sure you bring cash though because they don t accept credit cards. The service here is also nonexistent but that s usually how these restaurants are since you don t have to tip. The go to Fuzhouese breakfast is definitely the peanut noodles with a bowl of wontons. Almost everyone you see eating there orders that and it s just a classic.
Nice and cheap Chinese food. Not very clean the place, but the food was very good.
Pork and chives are delicious and not expensive.

This is a great hole in the wall. The pork and chives dumplings are very well made. You can also buy a frozen bag of 50 dumplings. The peanut noodles are great. The fish balls are traditional fuzhou style with meat in the center. The wontons have extremely thin skin and very little meat which is typical of that region.
only $12.50 I recommend the dumplings!
I liked everything I tried. Economical and very tasty. If you can, go.
detailed_reviews.review_translated_text: Me gusto todo lo que probe. Economico y muy sabroso. Si pueden, vayan.

detailed_reviews.review_text: Amazing!! So delicious, very affordable.
Cash only, come prepared. The noodles with peanut sauce somehow is not as  creamy as before they moved, but it is still good.
Affordable and great tasting food. Ordered the pork and chive dumplings and the peanut noodles. Would definitely come back!!
My favorite dumplings in all of NYC. Your $10 would go a long way here! I love all the dumplings they serve and the Wheat Peanut noodles. Simple, Delicious and Affordable! Love this place so much!
Peanut noodles were ok but very one dimensional peanut flavor even after adding some of their chili oil. Fish ball soup was pretty good, but I havent had this enough other places to really compare.
One of the best dumplings I ve ever tasted
Delicious
Try the peanut butter noodles.  Brink you own bottle of water.

50 frozen dumplings for $12 is an amazing deal. The dumplings are pretty big too.
Not sure why the ratings are so high. We were quite disappointed with the food. The place is no frills with quick service and friendly staff but the food was lacking. It was super cheap though.
This is the best cheap eats in Chinatown. I ve been here since 2012, always my go to if I m in Chinatown

Decent place for a no frills food but please know they do NOT have soup dumplings. We thought the food was just ok, not bad but not great. The staff was friendly and we got our food rather quickly (less than 10 mins?)
Visited 3 years ago, they changed location but theyre still fantastic. Highly recommended.

Amazing food and extremely affordable. An absolute must visit and your best option for good Chinese food/dumplings. The place is not much to look at, but that doesnt take anything away from the fantastic food.
Dumplings are super delicious
Absolutely delicious! Wonderful dipping sauce for the dumplings! Great value!
Fast service, yummy dumplings fish bowl soups and pasta with peanut sauce! Excellent price! Highly recommend!

This is one of my favorite places to go to for a quick and cheap meal. The food is always delicious, I ve never had any complaints. My go to meal is the wheat noodles in peanut butter sauce and (small) pork and chive dumplings which comes out to $5.50 (CASH ONLY). You order and pick up your food at the counter (in 5 mins or less) and can sit anywhere. You are to clear your area after you re done eating, which I don t mind doing, but sucks when others don t. The place is not the cleanest, sometimes the tables might have something spilled on it or a bit of food on it but that s because there s no table service therefore workers don t come around to clear and clean the tables. Either way, I love this place. Highly recommend
Best Chinese food I have ever had. A must in NYC

a spot so good and cheap that you almost want to keep as your own little secret. highly recommend the wheat peanut noodles and either of the pork dumplings (and for the dumplings make sure you use their provided soy sauce, it really is special) - can t beat the price or taste anywhere else!

Delicious pork and chive dumplings. Food is far better than the atmosphere but the food is definitely worth it. Next time will probably take the food to go and sit someone nearby outside in nice weather. Was able to have dinner for two for less than $10 which is a feat in NYC

Delicious food. We tried the Chicken and Mushroom Dumplings and also the Pork and Cabbage Dumplings. They were incredible. We had arrived based on the recommendation of the Food Insider YouTuber when she was looking for the best Dumpling in New York. The fish ball soup is pretty good, and the whole wheat noodles with peanut butter sauce are great. The best of all is the price-quality ratio. Since it was very very economical for us. You can eat on site.
detailed_reviews.review_translated_text: Riquisima la comida. Probamos los Dumplings de pollo y hongos y tambien los de cerdo y repollo. Estaban increibles. Habiamos llegado por la recomendacion de la youtuber de Food Insider Cuando buscaba el mejor Dumpling de Nueva York. La sopa con bolas de pescado esta bastante bien, y los fideos integrales con salsa de mantequilla de mani estan geniales. Lo mejor de todo es la relacion precio calidad. Dado que nos resulto muy muy economico. Se puede comer en el lugar.

detailed_reviews.review_text: Local located in the Chinese neighborhood of Manhattan. Very good food but the place leaves a lot to be desired in cleanliness and presentation Better to buy to take away. Good prices and quality in preparation. Quick to deliver orders.
Excellent food, fast service and very good prices. Best: pork and cabbage dumplings
detailed_reviews.review_translated_text: Excelente comida, atencion rapida y precios muy buenos. Lo mejor: pork and cabbage dumplings

detailed_reviews.review_text: Good here is cheap and really good. Since the first time I have tried it, I have been back a lot. Their wonton soup is different and really good. They only have steamed dumplings but they are also very good. I always see a lot of people here and today they had a longer line than before but went by fast.

Good soup, and noodles, we ate 2 and 12 and we didnt finish it. I still come back after 2 years and its still very delicious, I wish they put salt on the table... If youre from MX, buy a lemon on the corner
detailed_reviews.review_translated_text: Buena sopa, y noodles  comimos 2 con 12 y no lo acababamos.. Sigo viniendo despues de 2 anos y sigue muy rico, ojala pusieran sal en la mesa... Si eres de MX compra en la esquina un limon

detailed_reviews.review_text: peanut butter noodles and dumplings is the best, service is great and price is awesome! they offer dine in as well.

My new favorite place for dumplings! Got the tripe soup, peanut noodles and a pack of 50 frozen pork and chive dumplings to go. The tripe soup was jam packed with lots of trip & beef - great value for $4.5 0 (Large). The peanut noodles were very plain, but very flavorful! The dumplings were by far the best though. The skin is perfect (not too thin or thick) and the filling to skin ratio perfect. Hesitant to write this review as I do not want the prices to start rising, but this place is a must eat.
Great restaurant. The peanut sauce noodles were super tasty. I had a lot of food for $9.50. Also the bathrooms are very clean
Good value for money snack.
Very tasty and very good price. Quick service    Just top

Good food price is right. Large fishball soup Large wonton soup Large order of pork n chive dumplings Large order of pork dumplings Noodle in peanut sauce All for 18 dollars.  We ate too much n went into food coma.  Nap time

It s very affordable place, where mostly everything on the menu is below $5, great to order a lot to try but not empty your wallet. However the taste is just ok, noodles are under flavor, but dumpling is good. Dine in: Yes Outdoor seating: No Takeout: Yes
Always delicious and always prepared quickly, plus the price is incredible!
Amazing
