Great dollar to value
The menu is simple, the food is good and delicious, and the price is still cheap even up a little. What else do you want?

Shu Jiao Fu Zhou is very much a hole-in-the-wall eatery, located in the Lower East Side. the interior is messy and gritty, especially during busy hours. it is very divey and actual. there are some tables if you want to dine-in. order at the counter, tell them whether it s takeout or dine-in,  and wait for your food number to be called. it s CASH ONLY. was here recently and order takeout: fish ball soup (small) as well as the wheat noodles in peanut sauce. both hit the spot on a cold winter evening when i got home. a light dinner that was satisfying. the fish balls came in a clear flavorful broth with 6 fish balls. the fish balls were tender, carb-y, had the fish umami, and were filled with a little pork. the wheat noodles in a light peanut sauce were really good they had those carb-y fatty calories that your winter hunger wants. if you come here, order the steamed pork-chive dumplings as they don t miss. the fish ball soup (small) and the wheat noodles in peanut sauce are $2.75 each. staff are quick and my food was packaged and bagged neatly.

Unfortunately I didn t have the best experience here. I think the heater was broken and it was the day after the snow storm so our food got cold extremely fast. Despite that the peanut noodles still held up. I have better dumplings elsewhere but the noodles were pretty good.

Shu Jiao serves standard Fuzhou dishes like peanut flavored noodle, wonton soup and various boiled dumplings.  I have included a picture of their new location on Grand St.  I believe they used to be located near Allen Street and now moved.  The prices are very affordable and the quality for the price is very good.  For a quick stop for Chinese fast food, this place is worth a visit, wont hurt the wallet much.
Nice place, very fast, very affordable especially for Manhattan
Cheap eats in Chinatown! Got 2 small dumplings plates, wonton soup, wheat noodle with peanut butter, and a small fish ball soup - all for $13.75! Cash only.

I just wish I didnt have 0 stars. I bought a bunch of takeaways and was reminded to give me more sauce, but it turned out. . On a. You don t even give people sauce when you hold a tour, why are you still holding it? Are you so stingy in business?

We ordered the peanut noodles, pork dumplings, fish soup, and fish ball soup all for just $11--amazing value! The food tasted great, especially for the price. Very homestyle Chinese meal--we definitely enjoyed this on a cold night after arriving in NYC. The peanut noodles were good--it came with a lot and the sauce was flavorful though we do wish there was more of a peanut flavor. The pork dumplings tasted pretty authentic and home made. The filling was nicely seasoned! Could easily eat without any soy sauce. The fish soup tasted AMAZING. The flavor in the soup is something I crave every day now. The fish is very hard to eat, though, because of the amount of bones. The fish ball soup was had a pretty different flavor, but was good as well. Definitely not as strong as the fish soup.
Best value and dumplings you can get anywhere.
Fresh and yummy food at an incredible price. The best combo! Places like this makes me smile :)
The best  . Only downside is u gotta bring cash, but worth it a million times over.

I love this place! Havent been able to go back to China over the pandemic and this was a nice taste of home. The dumplings and the peanut noodles were my personal favorite. Would temper your expectations for the ambiance though. Its like they opened up a little hole in the wall shop in a shipping container. But Id happily sit in a shipping container for the quality and value of the food. Dont forget to BRING CASH. No credit cards allowed.
Serves amazing dumplings and noodles, almost always a line but the service is very fast, only accepts cash

Such a good Chinatown steal! The prices are low and the quality is top notch! We got the Peanut noodles and Pork and Chive Dumplings and it was so full of flavor. The amount is generous so definitely worth the long lines!
Fantastic dumplings. Fav is the pork and chives. Definitely buy some frozen ones to take home.
delicious and easy 10 boiled dumplings for $4.50 Unlimited spicy sauce The noodles are also large in size and have plenty of beef organ meat. The only drawback is that you can only use cash
I ask for no scallions for my food. They get me scallions and I ask for change, they got me the same dish just remove the scallions on the top. Cant give higher than one star
Do yourself a favor and check this place out. Fast, inexpensive, and delicious. Pork and chive dumplings are a highlight.
Fresh and incredibly cheap. Highly recommend.
Fast service quick soup and filling

TLDR: Best pork and chive dumplings in the city. Have been going here for years, including the prior location on Eldridge & Broome. I also love that they are open in the morning (versus others closer to noon). Perfect hangover food - don t forget to ask for a side of broth (the water they cook the dumplings in; they top off with chives/scallions). Fish ball soup is also a nice accompaniment. See example in the pic (from prior Eldridge location)- after a night out, nothing beats this trifecta of dumps, noods, and soup. Maybe something pickled on the side for acid P.S. Peanut noodles are a nice carbo-load side if you re going for a workout / day drinking sesh later.

This is tasty cheap Chinese food in Chinatown. We got the pork ball soup and the noodles with peanut sauce. For a total of $5 can t beat that! We were able to grab a table at lunch on a Monday but it was pretty packed with a line to the door.
The dumplings are delicious and the price is very cheap
Dumplings are delicious
get the noods and the dumps for optimal happiness
$4 for 10 dumplings!!! So tasty. Cash only! Wish I tried more but still so good for a quick bite

Fish ball soup is amazing. The peanut wheat noodles are pretty good but not enough peanut butter sauce. Dumplings are good too but I usually buy them frozen to enjoy at home. Cheap and quick lunch spot
Peanut Noodles were pretty good and their pork dumplings with chives were also really good. Best if you dine in and eat cause if you bring it to-go it won t be as good anymore
Great food with cheap price! The noodle and dumplings are good.
Easily the best $2.50 I can spend in the city. I don t eat meat but the dumplings & soups looks great they have some professionals in the kitchen cooking up a storm
Great place for brunch. Nostalgic, peanut noodles tasted just like the ones from the instant noodle packs in China, and the dumplings were good, skins a bit thick. Beef ball soup was ok.
This place has several great items on the menu.  The peanut butter wheat bodies are great (add a bit of chili oil to them) and the dumplings are on point.  Cash only.
Very reasonable prices .
AMAZING. Got 2 plates of dumplings, a plate of noodles, and a couple of bottles of water for under $15. AND IT WAS DELICIOUS. Highly recommended and will be back next time Im in NY.
The spectacular dumplings! They look homemade, and they are very good. The place is not very aesthetically pleasing, but we really liked the food, and it is very well priced.
High quality but for some reason the dumplings are a little sweet :(

We enjoyed some excellent dumplings. The restaurant is not very nice. It doesnt feel very clean. The floor is actually metal like the inside of a shipping container. While we were there, an old lady came out of the back with a big tray of boiled entrails that she threw out in the main trash out front. You absolutely cannot beat the prices or flavor though. And, based on the other customers, it is most certainly NOT a tourist trap.

As a hole in the wall in Chinatown, this place is quite unique and has delicious food! I got an order of the noodles with peanut sauce and a small fish ball soup. The noodles were chewy and the sauce was peanutty and flavorful, awesome! I just wish they had some chili oil for me to add to it; it would have been the perfect combination. The fish balls were quite good as well, though the meat inside wasnt very flavorful. The fish ball outside was quite chewy though not as soft as I thought it would be. The soup it came with was really good too, especially after I added the white pepper. For $2 each (including tax, and since you pay first you dont need to pay tip), the noodles and the fish ball soup are definitely a great bargain! I also tried my friends steamed dumplings which were also good (the soy sauce they have there isnt strictly soy sauce and its really delicious - I want to find out what it is!). The skin was a bit thick, though it was quite chewy. Very simple meal, but quite satisfying and tasty! Downside is everything here is plastic :( [Edit Dec 4, 2021] Havent been here for ages and mostly forgot about it, but its great! Changed location and upgraded the inside, its no longer dingy and falling apart - theres now proper tables and chairs and lighting, much cleaner feeling too. Surprisingly, prices havent raised at all in the last two (or more) years, no idea how! My go-to is the large pork and cabbage dumplings which comes with ten pieces along with the peanut butter noodles. Cash only, $6.75 including tax for it all, amazing! The only downside of this place is the excessive use of plastic, which is actually what shu jiao in the name of the restaurant is. I guess thats how theyre able to keep the costs low, but its really awful for the environment.

The best dumplings in Chinatown!Peanut Butter Noodles are excellent (stir them up first).Make a small mixture of sciracha,soy sauce and a squirt of vinegar in the small tubs provided and dip away!You can practically order the whole menu with a twenty dollar bill.If youre headed to Vanessas Dumplings please do yourself a favor and walk 1 more block for a true Chinatown experience.Absolutely phenomenal food and your next favorite thing.UPDATE:December 2,2021- Location has moved to a newly remodeled spacious 30 seat eatery on Grand Street.Same great items.

Great place to get dumplings! Wonderful and will come back all the time to get my dumpling fix. Also got the peanut wheat noodles, and while good, I would save stomach space to just get more dumplings. Note: Cash only

Great place for a quick bite (service is fast) at a very reasonable price. During my brief visit to NYC I made sure to stop by several times to stock up on some peanut sauce noodles and handmade dumplings to go.
Awesome hole in the wall dumpling place. Nice owners, cheap food, fast service. Highly recommend

This spot is my absolute jam and delicious. For a little over $5, U can get an amazing meal (I like to go 4 a late breakfast) that sticks with U all day. My go 2 is a small order of pork and chive dumplings and a beef tripe soup.

Wish I could give a 4.5 star rating here. I got peanut noodles, pork/chive and chicken/mushroom dumplings, and some wonton soup. Each dish was $2.75 and I had trouble finishing it. The pork/chive dumplings were wonderful with their house sauce. I also loved the peanut noodles. The chicken/mushroom dumplings were just okay, same with the wonton soup. I had to wipe down my own table as other reviewers said, so it wasnt the cleanest. But for $11, Id definitely go back and try some other dishes.
BEST DUMPLINGS IN TOWN
Great food for the price. Would definitely come again.

Can t beat the price!! Pork scallion dumplings were okay. Had peanut noodle cause all people in this place were having it but I don t get the taste. I guess it s like mac and cheese version of Chinese childhood memory food?
Very authentic and tasty food!! Very nice to have one fish ball soup in a cold weather.

Excellent food!!!! I also love the guy from the cashier. Excellent guy. I love the 4a) pork and chives dumplings. I always order that and get 3 orders!

I am struggling on how to review this place.  The pork and chive dumplings were good!  However, the peanut noodles that people rave about were really bland.  I m not sure what all the hype is about. Price wise it s pretty unbeatable.

A large order of dumplings + the peanut noodles is one of the best meals under 7 dollars in all of NYC. Ive been frequenting Shu Jiao for years now and it never fails to disappoint for a quick and filling meal. The dumplings are my favorite in all of Manhattan, perhaps even in all of NYC. Will definitely miss the old location with the communal tables and squishing between locals and tourists alike, but the new Grand location is larger and more spacious. Definitely a must try.
Meat stuff rice balls is where it s at, so so so good. Dumplings good too, fish ball alright.

Best dumplings Ive ever had. Not even exaggerating! I thought I was here for their Buckwheat Noodles (Sesame Noodles), but I devoured the dumplings instead. Pork and chive never fails but these dumplings were special. Theyre extra plump and so juicy - I can tell they use a lot of fat in them. I enjoyed them so much that I bought 50 frozen ones, and they are so easy to boil at home. I think the total cost of a meal between my friend and I was about $12. This cheap eat is definitely one of the gems in Chinatown. Cant wait to come back!

2021 update: their new spot on Grand st is a big upgrade! A lot more spacious and organized. The food is still the same as old location. Prices have risen but only slightly, still very affordable. Highly recommend! --- tasty dumplings at great prices! cheaper, faster, and much tastier than vanessas !
Great dumplings at a very reasonable price!
One of the best restaurants in Chinatown. Excellent customer service with extremely low prices. Highly recommend to people whom hunting for FINE Chinese food.
Great food at low prices! The pork/chives dumplings were amazing, flavorful and juicy! Cash-only

Best frozen dumplings in Brooklyn!!!
We have been here for some many years. We are so glad they moved to a new location and still opened during pandemic. The taste is still the same, yummy! Best dumplings in the city!
Pork and chive dumplings are bomb
The leek dumplings are big and delicious. The environment can be improved.

Fifteen years living in NYC and I ve yet to find a better bang for my buck.  So fast and consistent. Pork & Chive and Chicken & Mushroom dumplings are A++ You might as well get the wheat noodles w peanut butter and wonton soup while you re at it. There are about 15 tiny silky wontons in the soup. Bring cash. You ll need $12 max per person including a drink and tip and that s really going wild.
Delicious dumplings and noodles, very affordable and addicting!
Very good
Very decent prices for tasty dumplings and noodles. Its clean and spacious in the morning when there are less people eating there. Plenty of condiments to compliment your dishes.
By far the best dumplings I ve had in Manhattan

Frozen dumplings are really cheap and delicious! $12 for 50 dumplings is a crazy price in NYC! Notice that they only take cash, so be prepared with that. A highly recommended Chinese store, especially for frozen food!
Their food is good
detailed_reviews.review_translated_text: Su comida es buena

detailed_reviews.review_text: Been on my radar, finally got to try! Peanut butter wheat noodles were special. Like many others said, its not straight peanut butter sauce but clearly its a major component. Not a stick to your roof situation and very unique, yummy, flavor. Kicked it up with their chili oil (a must!). Tried it first without but really this really took it to the next level. Also had their chicken and mushroom dumplings which were filled to the brim with a delicate skin. Very tasty! Cant beat the price... $5.50 and I was stuffed with all of the above! If youre getting takeout, make sure you fill a cup with the chili oil and any other condiments since dumplings dont come with any dipping sauce. If eating in, wouldnt be the worst idea to wipe your table down first.
Great food for a fantastic price, cash only.
The peanut noodles were ok.  Not very flavorful.  Maybe the noodles absorbed too much of the sauce, which made them seem overcooked, IMHO.   The wontons were fine.  I would not go back.

Tasty and cheap! I was told this is one of the best cheap Chinese restaurants and it was correct. For $20 we ate a lot. I would recommend the pork dumplings over the mushroom ones. The noodles were good as well. I also find the staff friendly as I followed their recommendations to order. Overal a place Id recommend for simple dumplings and a cheap eat.

Great prices on the whole menu. The dumplings do have remarkably thin skins, and my dumpling leftovers came out even better fried the next day. Peanut noodles were pretty basic. Orders came out seemingly randomly so I ended up having to wait for 20 minutes.

What a great experience. This is a hole-in-the-wall place in the heart of Chinatown. The restaurant was not too clean, but the food is fantastic. The dumplings are legit. The noodles with peanut butter sauce were succulent. The price does not disappoint as well. We spent under $40 for a family of four, and we still had leftovers. If you are willing to try something new and if you dont mind the appearance of the restaurant then this is the place for you.
I love thia place. They used to be like 3 blocks down. Now this location is bigger and busier
The best noodles and dumplings in NYC and cheaper than the worst noodles and dumplings in NYC. Go figure.

Excellent food in the most unlikely of places. Very cheap, probably the best value in the city. The dumplings are excellent, as are the fish balls, wontons and pork balls. They have moved to a new, larger location on Grand and Allen Street as of July 2021.
Love this place! My partner and I got the fish ball soup and two places of dumplings for $10. Quality is solid for the price. Highly recommend
Delicious affordable dumplings. They moved a block away so the restaurant is now at 295 Grand. Worth the extra walk though!
amazing dumplings! great deal on bags of frozen dumplings too

Went to this place looking for Fujianese-style peanut noodles. It was my first time trying this style of Chinese cuisine and I was blown away by everything I got to try: ban mian, pork and chive dumplings and the wonton soup. The dumplings were OUT of this world, hands down the best I ve tried so far in Chinatown. Ban mian was super tasty and the wheat noodles were handmade. The wontons were unlike anything I ever had before, translucent and the most delicate layers I ve seen floating in yummy soup. Enough food for 3 people with $12. The sign posted on the front said they were moving to Grand Street and I ll be sure to visit them at their new location
I found this place from a YouTube video and ever since that I ve always wanted to try it. This place is very good and has fresh/warm food. I highly recommend this place. It s one of my favorite spots
Low on cash , but still want some amazing dumplings this is the spot. Great service , fast,  hot food
Real fujian- style wontons and buckwheat noodles. Good breakfast. No dining in allowed

Ive sampled every dumpling spot in the lower east side, and this spot BY FAR HAS THE BEST DUMPLINGS! Thin, delicate dough, delicious, juicy pork and chive filled centers. Overall, the perfect texture and flavor. And the price cannot be beat. Not to mention, their peanut noodles are seriously addictive, and the wontons in their soup are delicate wisps that are lighter than air. I am SO happy Vanessas was too crowded for me one day, or else I would have never discovered this far superior dumpling gem.
Great hole in the wall restaurant to eat at. Get the peanut butter noodles with wontons and a side of steamed pork/chive dumplings.
Nice food there. Cheap and tasty. Great for snack
They are moving to 295 Grand Street soon!  Hope the prices stay as cheap as they have been for all their amazing food
Love this place. I always get that boiled dumplings and peanut noodles.

This place is hands down the gem of NYC. The two staff running the restaurant & kitchen were super fast and friendly. Only $4 for 10 dumplings that are so authentic. Highly recommend coming here. They only take cash so bring plenty with you. Write home about this place. It is legit
extremely great     the best of the best, taste and price.
Amazing. We got 40 dumplings and 2 peanut noodles and demolished it standing in the park nearby. Cant beat the price, or the flavor.

This place is the definition of a hole in the wall spot, but oh my god the dumplings are so good and so cheap.  Please don t let the looks deter you.  Stop by, grab a dozen or two for a few bucks and let your life be changed.

This place sells FRESH made to order quick bites and meals. we got heir peanut noodles and their pork and chive dumplings and their chicken and chive dumplings and HOLY cow. so FRESH hot and delicious! If your in this area and want some tasty authentic food, stop by here! an awesome hole in the wall that I will 100% come back to and recommend.

The price was insane and the dumplings genuinely blew my mind. Tasted just like home in China. The store was busy but not crowded, and the waiters were extremely friendly. We ordered the noodles, dumplings, and fish ball soup. The dumplings were my favorite. The filling was rich and juicy, while the skin was thin and chewy, while also soft. It melted right in my mouth. The noodles were a little light in terms of flavor, but I could taste the peanut butter. Fulfilling. The fish ball soup, well I overestimated how much we could eat, so we got a large (11 balls), but we could only eat two each. Overall, an extremely pleasant experience, and the final price came down to an insane $10.
Simply the best dumplings!

The literal definition of a hole in the wall but if you know you know! The wheat noodles in peanut butter sauce for the price you pay is decadent. They are the perfect combination of sweet and savory and I never tasted anything like it. The dumplings come out hot, fresh, and on a flimsy paper plate which somehow feels so fitting. This place doesn t get any points for ambiance but who cares about ambiance when you know how to make damn good authentic food. Although I never have cash on me I d go out of my way to get some for this cash only establishment any day.
This was my go-to place in Chinatown when I worked nearby. I love their dumplings and peanut butter noodles. So tasty!!
I LOVE THIS PLACE $6.75 for noodles and dumplings that taste amazing!! some of the best noodles and dumplings ive ever had they take venmo too which is rare for chinatown (thank you thank you)

Been coming to Shu Jiao Fu Zhou for a few years now and I highly recommend their dumplings! I usually get their pork and cabbage which is delicate and delicious. Whenever I am in China town its a must stop for me even just as a snack. They are super cheap too!
Good food at a great price. Saw the recommendation at YouTube and gave it a tryout.
Quick, cheap, and delicious! The service is fast.

Really great value. Its NOT fancy at all. Its a typical hole-in-the-wall place that the locals know about (vs Vanessas next door). Youll get more bang for your buck here and tastes more authentic. I recommend getting the bags of frozen pork and chive dumplings as theyre excellent!
Outstanding, really cool people and great cool place.
A must-eat if you come to New York to save money! ! Cheap and big bowl Thanks to the guy at Windsor Hotel for the recommendation! !

Wontons were really good. With only $2.75 you get a really tasty soup for warming up your hands in the winter. Not much meat in the wontons, but hey thats not the point of wontons! 12/6/20: back open with window service. Support support support. Really the best. You ll have a hard time finding a better deal - steamed dumplings and delicious peanut noodles for under $6 is amazing. A must visit in Chinatown.

hard to justify going to gourmet chinese eateries when I can get all the items from this place at a fraction of the price. authentic hole in the wall with food that is soooo delicious and affordable.  I diee.  all handmade.  this is also the only place I can get mini wontons !! at the moment during covid time, they are only selling fish balls ($5-10) and frozen dumplings - pork and chives or pork and cabbage (50 pieces for $11) out of the shop down the street at 18 eldridge.
The Food Was SO GOOD!You should come and try some when its open!
Amazing value for good Chinese fare. I live nearby and will return often

Authentic! Authenticity is what I look into when it comes to Chinese food in America. Doesn t matter if it s street food or a fancy restaurants. It s so authentic here. My aunties all married off to Fu zhou. The wheat noodle is just as they re in Fuzhou. Fish balls soup is not bad, no funky taste as it can get with some other places. The chive dumplings is exceptionally good as I am one who usually try to avoid chive dumplings. One of the only place I found open on Christmas Day during nighttime.

Visited here in October 2019 while on holiday from Australia and it was amazing. Cannot get better value anywhere, an inviting local atmosphere, and so delicious Im still thinking about the peanut noodles and dumplings half a year later. Favourite place we ate the whole trip, and hope to visit again one day after quarantine is over!
Best dumpling ever but closed (04/13/20)

Tell me how you hold chopsticks   Mr... good memories

Love them. Unpretentious & value for money!!!! It s a great place to have simple Chinese food in cold winter time!
Fast and friendly. Peanut butter noodles are an unusual but good choice.

Food is always on point! This is a local spot! For true New Yorkers . Price is always right! Cash only! Real deal! Dumplings and Peanut Noodles is the way to go! Come hungry and be sure to explore this iconic New York restaurant. Very fast and efficient!!! Top 10!!
Cheapest Chinese food place I ve ever seen in nyc

Right next to Vanessas Dumplings is one of the best hole in wall dumpling shops, and cheap meals in the city. Order by number there, the wheat noodles in peanut sauce are the best Ive ever had. Very good for the price.
Havent  benn but heard nothing buy good things
Pork and chive dumplings to die for.
The best dumplings in the city. Even better than at Vanessa s next door :)

Very quick, efficient and cheap spot for great tasing noodle dishes! Their noodles with peanut sauce are a must try. It can get pretty cramped here so be prepared to get take out if theres a line.
I like Wonton soup

Great noodles and peanut sauce. Also, the beef meatballs are interesting - I m guessing they are minced beef tendon mixed with corn starch and flash boiled.... tender enough but funky. High in protein.
Amazing dumplings, super cheap and fast

After seeing this restaurant on an Instagram page as a must try, I decided to try it out! I had the pork and chive dumplings, and they were amazing! Probably the best I ve ever had! This is deff a gem just make sure you have cash when you go!
Best dumplings Ive ever had. Also the cheapest. Their pork and chive dumplings are legendary. If Id ever visit NYC again, I would have at least one meal there again.
delicious

detailed_reviews.review_text: You can enjoy a variety of nice cultural food with a reasonable price.
Affordable, fast, delicious. Pork and chive dumplings are to die for with some soy and hot oil. Peanut wheat noodles are good...solid.
YUM the noods were scrumptious and super affordable

My gal pal brought me to this place one cold autumn night and I was hooked. The portions and ESPECIALLY the price works for my cheap asian self. Yes, I said it. Nobody wants to be spending $15 on each lunch meal! GTFO. lol We always get the ever so famous peanut butter noodles along with dumplings and our favorite but hardly ever mentioned in reviews - - beef with starch soup. It is perfect for 2. If you eating alone, just get the noodles + the beef w/ starch soup. Comfort food at the finest price. This place is super hole in the wall but it is one of my favorite spots. Cant beat the price and the people working there deserve the customers!!!
Cheap, but thats about it. Food was ok. Place could have been cleaner.
Some of the best asian food Ive ever had, definitely go here.
The best peanut noodles.

This is an original Chinese place to eat. The only person who could speak English was the one taking the orders. The food was okay but not great. The prices were good. It was a novel experience for us. I liked the dumplings more than the beef noodle soup.
Pretty good taste and fast serving speed
Super cheap, large portions, and delicious. $4 for 11 fish, $3.50 for 10 dumplings, $2.5 for noodles in peanut sauce

Id rather come here than the over crowded dumpling place a few doors down. Not only were the dumplings some of the better ones Ive had but the peanut noodles were so good! The fish balls were good as well. Id definitely come back here in a heartbeat
Food was bland
Best dumplings in NYC

Perhaps I have been spoiled silly with the other noodle options around, I find what is on the menu to be extremely bland and almost tasteless and one can find better noodles elsewhere. The stuffed fish balls which is supposed to be a Shu Zhou specialty tasted like mass produced stuff and there is nothing to shout about. This is shocking when the shop was full house after we arrived that we wondered whether here something wrong with our taste buds. The only redeeming point is that the prices are rock bottom and I dont think I can find anything else cheaper. So if you are looking to get filled up to get on the road and dont think too much about taste, this will be the best option around. Otherwise, there are better noodles elsewhere in Flushing Queens and beyond.
What can I say? Tasty Fu Zhou style Chinese food with a price thats hard to beat.
The dumplings are the best!
Food was good and good prices

1) Wheat noodles w/ peanut butter sauce 2) Pork & Chive dumplings (10 for $3.50!!!) Me and my partner got 20 dumplings and an order of noodles for $10. The pork & chive dumplings were some of the best Ive ever had. You can actually watch the staff making them on spot. Clearly masterful and amazing quality put into the product. It is cash only and there is seating within the restaurant. Highly recommend coming here. Some of the best dumplings in NYC!
Dumplings were amazing, pop in here on your way out of way back for a quick bite.  Very reasonable prices but just superbly tasty.

Saw a very high rating and wanted to check this place out. You dont come here for high quality food or great service; you come here for cheap good food that will fill you up for $10 or less. When you enter, you go up to the counter, look to what to order on the menu on the side and order your food. Then you seat yourself and someone will bring you your order. The food is by no means amazing, but its extremely cheap, especially in New York. I came in around 8:30PM and the place was decently packed. Its a very small restaurant, large groups are possible but may be difficult. If you enjoy eating alone then this is the place for you. I ordered 3 dishes which totaled to $10 and was full off that. I was a bit disappointed in the wonton soup since I was expecting large balls of meaty wonton but what I got was mostly skin and a bit of meat (see picture). But overall, I cant complain especially with the food being so cheap.
A must in NYC. Try everything. Cash only.

Absolute gem when it comes to simple, affordable Chinese food. The 2 things that are a MUST are the wheat noodles with peanut sauce as well as the pork and chive dumplings. The noodles are extremely chewy and tasty with the rich peanut sauce. The dumplings are an excellent paired food. They are stuffed with filling while melting in your mouth. Paired with a mixture of sriracha and soy sauce, it adds an excellent flavor change that is definitely needed while eating noodles. 100% must go.

Good food at super cheap price. If you are turn off by dirty looking place, do not come here as this isn t the place for you but if you want a good old Chinese fashion food, this is the place. Try the noodle soup or the dumpling (well that about all they have anyway), you can t go wrong.

Cheap eats no fuss dumplings and noodle shop.  Simple menu with various noodle and topping combinations as well as dry or in soup format.  Dumplings are made with skin and much cheaper than the shop down the street.  Thin skin as in wontons thin.  Personally I prefer eating less skin and more meat!  Just as delicious but this hole in the wall is pretty ghetto.

Veg Review: They have only one veg item on the menu and it is the peanut noodles. Get it get lit. Its 2.50 for a plate, get 2 plates if hungry. Its really tasty and is definitely recommended if you in the area. Love the hole in the wall!
fav place in chinatown
Yum! Wheat noodles with peanut sauce is everything.
Best dumplings and noodles for an outrageously low price. Not from NYC but this is the place I visit at least once every chance I get
Great food and the place was packed. Not a single bad thing to say. The peanut noodles are a must buy.

So cheap!  And people are nice, even though it seems like they are yelling all the time. I would stick to dumplings.  Dumplings are great especially for the value.  The soup I tried (pork dumpling soup) was kinda gross.  I was nervous about getting sick.  Tasted funky.  Very very affordable.  This place somehow managed to get A from the health department.
Really good and cheap. What else do you need?

Excellent noodles and dumplings. Id go back to this place. You can eat here for less than $10. Incredible, authentic, and quite the experience. Dining area is small, but you dont need much space.

my favorite spot in the hood for CHEAP foods for under $10! the service is kind, a bit old school- so make sure you have cash monies on you. the Sesame/Peanut Noodle is the best here. HUGE portion for the price you pay! I love mixing the noodles and slurping them. its such a comforting feeling. the Pork & Chive dumplings are delicious, but not the best in the area. again, for the price of $3 for six dumplings- i have nothing to complain about this place.
These dumplings. Such good quality. Such a great price. I live here now.
Amazing traditional food with fair prices. The peanut butter noodles are brilliant.

I think these might be the best dumplings in town, and Ive had a lot of dumplings. Excellent wrapper texture, which held together nicely but was thin, pliant and fine, not doughy. Filling had an incredibly deep and complex flavor and a soft, fresh texture, not compacted or chewy. I could have easily eaten 20 by myself. Plus, they have chili oil. You dont need it, or any topping, because the filling itself is that good, but I appreciate the spice option. On the other hand, their very popular peanut noodles didnt do it for me - somewhat watery sauce and not much to it. But those dumplings, Im in love.

$3.5 for 10 dumplings, $2.50 for peanut butter  noodles and $4 for wheat noodles with beef is unheard of especially in Manhattan. Served with plastic cutlery and orders made on the spot, truly delicious and definitely the cheaper and more authentic version compared to Vanessas dumplings next door.

Delicious and inexpensive! Plenty of seating with very friendly employees. Tonight was my first time there, and I ran into a friend whos a regular (its his favorite place to eat). 100% recommend!
One of the most delicious eats during my NY stay. An absolute phenomenal price!

Oh my goodness. The pork and chive dumplings are AMAZING. and you get 10 for $3.50???  Incredible. I have high standards for dumplings. Ive been making them since I was old enough to form memories. I lived in Sichuan province. I make dumplings every few months. I dont often justify buying someone elses dumplings but THESE are worth it. They could double the price and Id still buy them. Selling these dumplings for so cheap is borderline criminal. The skin is incredibly thin, theres a ton of filling, and the filling is well seasoned and juicy even before the addition of the delicious dumpling sauce. Dumplings here are truly the best I ve ever had in NYC and so cheap! The wontons in the wonton soup are mini wontons which I love but some might not. Also those peanut noodles.. I mean c mon.. they re cheaper than riding the subway to get here. Obvious but.. CASH ONLY!!
One of the best. Really cheap and amazing quality. The steamed dumplings are amazing Don t let the decor and entrance to scare you

This hidden gem should be on the map of secret food maps of NYC. Constantly busy, noisy, and full of flavorful food. They specialize in peanut sauce noodles, dumplings, and various soups. This is a cash only place, but even a few bucks can get you a large serving of dumplings! This place is so good that I had an internal struggle of whether to write a review and let the world know about it, or keep it selfishly secret.

Oh so good!!!! The dumplings are amazingly tasty, with the perfect amount of salt and softness of texture (as if I am an Asian food connoisseur). The best part is you get 12 for $6! Must try, for sure!!
great dumplings!

Its been a hot while since I have been. I have eaten at numerous dumpling places. I have been wanting to try this place again and boy am I glad. The skin is very soft. Some may say overcooked but it was tip toeing the line for me. The skin was thin which was more important to me. Now the filling, this was tasty. They were more heavy handed on the chives which prefer. The dumplings come out steaming hot and just a very small sip of porky juice. It has a nice blend of the chives and pork but there is this subtle sweetness that hints you just as you swallow. They are cheap as ever and a large serving of 10 would fill you up. There isnt any chili oil here but rather sriracha, soy sauce and black vinegar. You dont really need anything else to top the dumplings because they are flavored very well. The pork ball broth reminds me more of pork wontons with barely there skin. The broth has subtle fish flavor and tartness. I suspect that there is some vinegar. The soup looks simple but there is some complexity to it. Super nice and quick service. You might have to get cozy with your neighbors. Its a no frills place that serves yummy dumplings and other goodies
Delicious dumplings in a no frills environment, reasonably priced. This is a good spot for a quick bite, not a sit down restaurant. We liked

Okay. This place is a grungy dump - Im being kind! They use plastic utensils and styrofoam plates. I definitely would not go here for a first date... Unless you want to impress your date with absolutely fantastic dumplings and noodles for next to nothing. This place is right next to Vanessas, which is widely regarded as having the best dumplings in the area. After trying both, I have to say, this place is faster, cheaper and better in every way. It just isnt as pretty. Also, the peanut noodles are amazing. Even my wife and daughter, who HATE tripe, loved the beef tripe soup. On the downside, there really arent a lot of options - the menu is pretty brief. But what there is is really spectacular, especially for the price.

My favorite place for fj street food! Peanut butter noodles and fj wontons are great, but the boiled dumplings with soy sauce and vinegar are my favorite

The dumplings and Noodles in Peanut sauce are incredible. Love the simplicity, fixed menu offering and focus on the taste of the food that hits home in every visit. Good service, quick and pleasant. Far superior than a plot of the dim sum spots in the vicinity.

Want something authentic? This is it. Now dont go gentrifying this too.
The dumplings were good not a fan of the noodle soups.
Very simple presentation but the food is on point. Pork and chive dumplings add some sriracha to soy sauce then you are ready to go.
Best steamed dumplings that I ever had. Also enjoyed the peanut noodles
Best dumplings ever at incredible value ($3.50 for 10). The wheat noodles with peanut sauce are also excellent.
Enjoyed a variety of food excellent

I love this place! I used to live down the block and used to to go Vanessa s all the time but then figured I d give this little corner store a chance and haven t been back to Vanessa s ever since. Dumplings and peanut butter noodles are my go to and omg they are delicious!!! I moved out of the neighborhood 2 years ago and the only time I go back is to go to this restaurant.

Favorite Dumpling place in Chinatown hands down. Get the Fuzhounese combo of dumplings and peanut noodles. The staff is very kind and the seating is limited-- people often share. The turn over is very quick. Also Ive enjoyed buying the bag of 50 for $10 and boiling them at home. Still just as tasty!

It s a hidden gem in Chinatown. You can get 10 dumplings, one noodle and soup for just $10. It s rarely find in NYC. Also, their dumplings were one of the best I got in NYC too. Very thin skin and flavorful filling.
Favorite dumplings in the city! You can get a full meal for $6 (get the peanut butter noodles and dumplings). Delicious food and no frills.

I visited here to have warm authentic chinese food. It was perfect place that I wanted. And I couldnt believe the price. Two dishes were 5$ and tastes so good. I especially loved the dumplings. Also workers at there were so nice.
Great hole in the wall for a quick bite. Get the dumplings, peanut sauce noodles and fish ball soup. Cash only.

A great hole in the wall,, Dumplings are good at best.. I buy them made, great price! $10.00  for a bag of 50! Just popem into boiling water for 10 mins. And feel like youre sitting with 6 strangers at the Restaurant all over again and again and again....

Amazing hole in the wall place in Chinatown. Dumplings and peanut noodles are tasty and very cheap. We always leave stuffed and happy at $6 a person. The seating is basic and a bit crowded, but service is nice and efficient. Great place to take away as well. I always like to make it back when visiting NY!
Excellent food at excellent prices! Best dumpling Ive ever had
These dumplings were bomb! Thin wrapping, juicy pork, and fresh chives. Super cheap too.  A must try if youre in the area. Not super clean, but the food is amazing.
Got an order of pork & chive dumplings and the peanut noodles for a total of $6. Great flavor and quick service. It s an awesome hole in the wall and I ll definitely be back!

Amazing to find a place like this in New York... great dumplings, great soup, great noodles, great noodle soup! There are some things in New York that are hard to figure out the economics, the food is so good, but the prices are so reasonable. 10 pork and chive dumplings for $3.50 as of February 2019, beef with starch and thin or thick rice noodle soup, $4. Both very tasty, both very filling, no corporate garbage dressed up to look like something its not..tiny portion baloney here.  You get more than you pay for; if I lived across the street I might eat three meals a day here.
Stick with the dumplings and noodles
A very satisfying, quick bite
Delicious dumplings at a really cheap price. Service is super quick. The place is not fancy, but its totally worth the experience!
They have the best dumplings in the city. They re cheap and so delicious.

Trust a Chinese - this place does delicious and honest dumplings. You can get 10 for just $3.50 and they do not skimp on the ingredients, each dumpling is generously loaded with meat and chives/ cabbages and are juicy on bite. Will definitely be back every single time I come to NY!

The foods quality or taste has not changed in the four years that I have been coming here. The food is cheap,delicious, and the service is fast. I prefer it over Vanessas which is a couple doors down. I recommend the pork and chive dumplings,peanut wheat noodles, and a cold herbal tea.
Delicious peanut butter noodles and pork chive dumplings
Cash only

So, heres the thing. The pork and chive dumpling were awesome. But this is not a restaurant in any sense of the word. You will walk in, pay, sit, and they will bring you your food on styrofoam. In about 15 minutes you will be on your way. They dont serve water or tea, that sort of thing. So on the service front, its really a 1-2 star kind of experience. Honestly, there is no decor and there is no service. The place is runned down. The dumplings though were a solid 5 stars. So I am honestly thinking of this as a 3-4 star kind of experience, based largely on the pork and chive dumplings. But because this is a place where you can sort of fill up for about $10 per person, I am edging that up to 4 stars. Additionally, the soup ordered wasnt really memorable. It was served in a plastic take-out container. One time, I walked here to check it out given its great reviews and the girl I was with was like, no. And I think she had it right. While the dumplings are rated highly, we need more than this. There isnt much complexity to the menu items. We are kind of a fan of the dumplings but that was really the sole attraction experienced so far.
Incredible dumplings
Wow, great amount of quality food for very little money. I had soup and dumplings, both were fantastic.
I never not crave for those peanut noodles and dumplings!
Incredibly cheap eats in New York City. A plate of 10 dumplings is just $3.5 and its delicious.

$5 for awesome peanut rice noodles and fish ball soup. Could have gone for excellent pork dumplings as well. So much good for so little. Its a marvel. Perhaps not the last word on food in Chinatown, but a visit is a reward for yourself.
Good food for small money!
Cheap delicious food, cant go wrong
Very good food! And for so cheap!
Great and cheap dumplings. Simple and not fancy but for $3.50 for 10 dumplings, I would come here every day if I could!
Delicious noodles with peanut butter sauce for $2
Very simple and authentic dumplings and soup. Sadly I am too much of a westerner to like the real authentic dishes like beef tripe, but the dumplings and fish ball soup were good.
Good steam dumplings

There are not many hole-in-the-wall Chinese restaurants that make quality food in the ever-gentrifying Manhattan Chinatown, so Im glad Shu Jiao Fu Zhou still remains in operation. I first stumbled to this restaurant when I found out that my favorite restaurant that I usually go get Noodles with Peanut Butter Sauce was closed down for good. This restaurants most popular dish is also Noodles with Peanut Butter Sauce (#5), and its just as good. Shu Jiao Fu Zhou emphasizes the food that they serve more than the setting that they serve it at. Sure, the place will be tremendously better off with a major restaurant renovation, but yet groups of people still come and eat here. Its usually a Russian Roulette situation whenever I visit this place; either the setting was untidy or the food was bland...I have witnessed either one of those conditions out of all my visits.
Very tasty. Prices are incredibly cheap. Very tight space but they sell frozen dumplings to prepare at home.
Typical and delicious!
detailed_reviews.review_translated_text: Tipico y delicioso!

detailed_reviews.review_text: Great authentic food

Despite its shabby looks, this place is a real gem, with great food at amazing prices   a meal for two will be easily under $20. I only wish there were more on the menu, as it is a bit limited. We liked both varieties of dumplings, slightly preferring the pork and cabbage. The peanut noodles were excellent as well. Service is very fast.

Everyone knows about Vanessa s Dumplings - walk down a random NYU dorm hallway or stop the first Danish tourist you see carrying a Lonely Planet, and ask them where to get dumplings in Chinatown. They ll probably tell you to go to Vanessa s. on Eldridge Street. If things are really dire, they might even send you to the 14th Street location, or the one on Bedford Avenue. But here s the truth: Vanessa s Dumplings is kind of bad. They re not bad, say if you re at a strip mall in Connecticut. But they re thick and often greasy, and more importantly, all you need to do is walk about 20 steps to have what might be the best dumplings in Manhattan. On the corner of Broome and Eldridge, about a quarter block up from Vanessa s, is Shu Jiao Fu Zhou, a spot you could easily walk by without noticing - no less going in. Don t make that mistake. For $2, you can get 6 perfectly steamed, smooth, truly delightful dumplings with a pork filling that is almost sweet. They don t come fried, and if you can t deal with that, you don t really deserve to be here anyway. For $3, you can have 10, and for an extra $2, you should add on a plate of their also delicious wheat noodles with peanut butter sauce. Or, by all means, go eat a thick doughy orb with a bunch of teenagers next door. Your move.

This hole in the wall joint is cheap, fast, authentic and most importantly delicious. They have been in business for almost all of my life--I grew up right across the street. With the gentrification of the neighborhood, they are finally getting the recognition (on blogs) that they deserve. Their peanut butter egg noodles and their pork leek dumplings are some of the best you will ever have! Everything tastes like how my mom would make it and every item on the menu is under $10. Pro tip--grab a bag of frozen dumplings to go for 10-minute dinner or potluck party! xo, Farrah at NST Pictures
Yummmmmm
detailed_reviews.review_translated_text: Yummmmm

detailed_reviews.review_text: Best Dumplings
A delicious hot soup for the cold of NY.
detailed_reviews.review_translated_text: Una rica sopa caliente para el frio de NY.

detailed_reviews.review_text: Get the wheat peanut butter noodles. Quite good, and better than the Think Peanut Butter Noodles...It was a bit disappointing to realize that they offered no drinks that were made in-house, just Coke and fake iced tea.
Real Chinese food without going to China.
Tiny place.  AMAZING FOOD.  TASTY.

You can buy tasty and cheap food in most places in Chinatown  but Place should be cleaned up. Its very grimy. Service can be better. They seem a little prejudiced when a non mandarin speaker but chinese person orders in another dialect which they can totally understand and speak since i heard them speak it before and totally understand my requests. I sense the prejudice.  A business should not exude that behavior to any kind of customer.  After all they are in Chinatown where people speak different dialects.
Simple menu at a very reasonable price. Typical FJ food, you can still get a meal for less than $5. Good food from a hole in the wall.
Everyone says try this noodle dish, try that noodle dish...NO do yourself a favor and just order a million dumplings and go to town on that. Wonton soup was pretty great too but DUMMMMMMMPLINGS!!!!

Came here to grab a bite after visiting PanIQ Room right next door. The PB noodles were excellent and just the right amount of peanut butter sauce. Definitely preferred the wheat noodles over of the rice noodles as it pairs much better. Boiled dumplings were also excellent - fresh and hot. Cheap food in a no frills setting with quick service. Cant get any better!
Good food

If you enjoy boiled/ steamed dumplings, this spot may not look like much BUT this place is better than Vanessa`s Dumpling House next to this PLUS the customer service is wonderful!!! If you eat there, they will bring you your order to the seating area. THE FOOD IS SO GOOD BOTTOM LINE!!! #repeatedcustomer

Its a fast food Chinese noodle place. One of many around Chinatown. This one is above average with good food at rock bottom prices. There is no atmosphere, but its not to be expected in this type of place. Its a; You order... Food comes fast... Eat and leave!!! You do not want to linger here. But, you cant do any better for this type of experience. Worth a visit...

I had an early flight, so my favorite place for dumplings wasnt open for breakfast. I found Shu Jiao Fu Zhou on Yelp with pretty good reviews, so I came. I ordered the beef and wheat noodles soup, pork and cabbage dumplings, and pork and chives dumplings. My beef and wheat noodles soup was super bland. The beef was good, but the whole bowl just needed a lot of seasoning. I added a bit of soy sauce, vinegar, and sriracha. The dumplings were okay, nothing special. I make better dumplings at home. But their prices cant be beat. Its much cheaper here than the other dumplings places I like. My favorite dumplings places are 88 Lan Zhou, Nan Xiang XLB( Flushing, NY), and Vanessas.
Very yummy and fresh taste and great deal
Wow this food is amazing and cheap
tasty

This place has really good peanut butter noodles and dumplings. My go to spot for cheap, affordable lunches and the portion sizes are extremely reasonable for the price point. I love coming here but dont expect it to be a nice comfortable place to sit down. If you can get past that, this is the spot to go!
Enjoyed the fish balls and dumplings, and prices were insanely cheap. The noodles and soups were extremely simple but not bad.
Go for their wheat noodles with peanut sauce. So worth it and its only $2.50
Gosh darn the food is good here. And they have a gosh darn A rating from the health dept. and they speak english if thats your thing.
Best 2-3 dollars you can spend on food! Love the dumplings (10 for $3) and peanut noodles ($2)!! Also the restaurant has a health grading of A, which is really good to know.
No frills Chinese food spot. Had peanut noodle, large order of dumplings, and a small order of fish ball soup for $8.50. Enough for two. Hard to beat that in NYC!

One of the good cheap eats in the city. I ve been twice and had the same experience each time. I tried their sour vegetable with noodle soup and it was good. It s a decent size bowl of noodles and green veggies, great especially on a wintery day. The wheat noodle with peanut sauce is tasty as well. You can t get this quality for this price elsewhere. The place is small and it s nothing fancy, just good, cheap comfort food. They re cash only, but you don t need to bring much considering you can buy a couple things for $5.
Delicious food, and very VERY inexpensive, highly recommend!
The best place in the world ! Omg I love the peanut noodles ! Love itttttt .
Get the dumplings.
Greatest place to try Fu Zhou food.  Will come here for multiple times.
The decoration is poor and the environment is not very clean.
Delicious boiled dumplings and peanut noodles. I dont know whats in there but its like crack. Nice staff but the bladerunner appearance might be off-putting.

This place was awesome!! DO NOT come here expecting a quiet ambience and table service. The dumplings were cheap yet really good. Always fresh! I highly suggest this place because of the quality of food. Do remember that the service is hectic and the restaurant is small. There is usually no seating but they do have one table that can accommodate a large group. Try to get your food before sitting though!
Extremely cheap and delicious. $6 for 10 steamed dumplings and a giant plate of peanut noodles.
Excellent pork and chicken dumplings. This is the real deal. No fuss--just delicious dumplings.
The wheat noodles in peanut butter sauce was unexpectedly tremendous.
Best dumplings around.
Definitely got there for their dumplings
Cheap and quick and good
Peanut butter noodle = heavenly
Hands down, the best dumplings in the City.
Wheat noodles!
These dumplings are a teleporter to Mainland China.
Good, Fast and cheap. Did i say Good!

Best chives and pork dumplings I have had. They are full dumplings, and the flavors remind me of a home. What was most surprising was the rice and wheat noodles in peanut butter sauce. Who knew peanut butter would go so well with noodles???
Really good.
Dumplings are made fresh so give them 5-10 min but it s totally worth it! You get 10 for $3.50. Also had the tripe soup with noodles and also a hit! Definitely recommend this local gem!
The dumplings were amazing and the food was marvelously affordable. They are cash only so come prepared for that. But you can easily feast in excess with a $20 in hand.

My go-tos are the dumplings with their wonton soup. I do not believe they pan fry their dumplings but their boiled dumplings are superb. The dumpling skin is nice and thin while durable enough to hold the flavorful filling. Fuzhou style Wonton soup is great especially during winter months. This is place ideal if you are trying to eat good on a budget while in lower Manhattan.

This place doesnt offer much by way of charm or ambiance, but it has shockingly low prices for delicious food. I got 10 boiled pork chive dumplings and a Coke for $4.50. I found the dumplings to be tastier than Vanessas dumplings, which is nearby and seems to garner more hype. I will definitely be going back.

I got noodle with peanut butter sauce [$2.5] with pork dumplings [6 pieces for $2.5]. It came out $5 in total. Although the place is not that big and there is not a lot of selection in the menu, IT IS SO DAMN CHEAP and can make an adult full like with the ones i just got. You can see in the picture that the plates arent that small. ONLY WITH $5 you can get full. This place receives a 5 Stars.
Best fish balls.
Cheap as hell
This is the amazing place and the food is awesome
Great pork and chive dumplings!
Great wonton soup. The rest of the food is really good also. You dont go here for Ambiance you go here for food. You will be pleased.
Best duppings in downtown Manhattan

It was the last 5 minutes until closing and I was caught in traffic prior, I would expect them to say no that they are closed but just for some noodles they took care of me. I will definitely come back because of how I was treated.
Hole in the wall, no frills. Amazing dumplings
Deliciius, fast, inexpensive food.

Visited on 5/5/18 its currently 5/8/18 me and my wife both got food poisoning from this place. Me and my wife shared 2 of the 3 orders of dumplings we ordered pork and chive. The 3rd order we have to a homless person god rest his soul. The dumplings were nasty as all heck. The place is so small and crowded that ordering food is a task. The place also smelled weird and funky like pig poop. I regret eatting here so much. The next night after eatting here me and my wife became violently sick. I have a blister on my lip and a minor throat infection as well LITERALLY OVER NIGHT! My wife had violent diahreah. I had to force myself to throw up just to get relief from my stomach pain and gas..... I hate this place and almost wish I could sue or something.

Surprisingly good for what it is. Had the dumplings, they were amazing. Fish ball soup is also very good. My girlfriend is from Fuzhou and according to her, this place has the best Fuzhou food of any place she has had in the city. The prices are also very low, which is fantastic.
Good taste good price

Not your usual Chinese food: this small, simple-looking Chinatown restaurant serves dishes from the unique cuisine of a coastal Chinese region, and does so perfectly. The peanut butter noodles are a simple but perfect - add some Sriracha and youre in for a treat.
Great traditional Fuzhou food.

A total hole-in-the wall with very limited seating and a modest selection, but hands-down some of the best steamed dumplings we ve ever had. Two $3 orders of 10 dumplings each filled the two of us to the brim! Will be back and highly recommend.

Hole in the wall place (you dump your foam plates and other garbage after you eat in a black trash bag that just sits open in the back of the restaurant) that specializes in $3 for 10 pork and cabbage dumplings which are excellent and tasty. They do not have soup dumplings fyi. They also have a noodle with peanut sauce dish that everyone else seemed to be ordering but I didnt get a chance to try it (but will next time.)
The best experience ever! I highly recommend this restaurant to all food lovers out there!

Simple, delicious food at a great price. The owners are lovely, hard working people and I love the down to earth atmosphere here grabbing a bite to eat after work amongst locals from the neighborhood.

Quick, inexpensive food, in a order-then-grab a seat and bus your table atmosphere. Everything is boiled, nothing fried so you wont smell like grease after going here. Food: - peanut noodles - nice flavor, more flavorful. Basically noodles with a little scallion - dumplings - 10 boiled ones for $3 or 6 for $2. The filling is less salty and fatty than other places. Its also got a lot of scallion.  I prefer this over the oilier versions at other places. - Beef with starch in wheat/rice noodle soup - the meat is a little weird - chewy/bouncy, a decent quantity of it.  The soup is a simple broth and has some chopped napa cabbage and a little scallion as well. Overall this dish is on the blander side.
Price is hard to beat, quality wise, it is better than one would expect.
Where else can one fill their stomach with a tasty noodle plate for $2?  Expect no ambiance however, its all in the food.
I loved paying only $5 for two dishes, but the food did not live up to the hype for me. Not bad, but not the best dumplings in NYC.

Best dumplings in NYC. Youll smell like garlic for the rest of the day since they use garlic chives, but its so worth it - and if anyone asks you thats just an opportunity for another Shu Jiao Fu Zhou convert. (Dont be scared of the mid-renovations exterior appearance, either - its always looked like that.)
If i could give them 10 stars I would!!! I adore the dumplings here, they are so good! I usually buy two bags of frozen dumplings, 50 dumplings for $10. I always have them in the freezer.
The Place to grab quick dinner when I was in NY. Fast in fast out. Great food that leaves you wanting for me. Last I had them was 4 years ago, but I still had great memories of the place and food.
Awesome noodles. Awesome dumplings. The price also makes you forget that you re in NYC.
Great dumplings, soup lacks of taste but overall good food.
The best Fu Zhou cuisine in Chinatown and Flushing. Authentic and cheap. You can buy their delicious dumpings frozen at $10 for 50.
Cheap and delicious, it would be great if the environment could be cleaner!
Dont get fooled by appearances. These are the best soup dumplings in Manhattan. Try for yourself.
Amazing pork Chive dumpling. Very cheap too
Great food, super cheap
Full marks for fish balls/dumplings/flat meat! ! The smell of grandma.
Excellent cheap dumplings, come here over nearby Vanessas any time

A guy we shared a cab with recommended this place, said he was coming from somewhere out in the boroughs all the way into the city for dumplings.  I wondered what sort of dumplings would drive a man on such a journey.  I found out.  $3 gets you a paper plate with 10 huge fresh steamed dumplings the likes of which I have never tasted before.  When you bite into them they burst with unique flavor.  I found myself going back for ten more, and ten more....the next day too.  This place sits right next to a much fancier looking dumpling house that looked a bit too hip and expensive for my taste, so dont be fooled.  The one on the corner is the one you want.
Good enough dumplings for cheap $
Hidden gem. Incredible dumplings at unbelievable prices. They also make hearty soups. Have the beef tripe one or the fish ball one. And the peanut noodles is to die for.
Very authentic Chinese food

A dumpling shop of the highest order. Pork dumplings are delicate and less doughy  (similar to Lam Zhou) and bursting with flavor. Eager to try other things on the menu - noodles and soups looked excellent. Service was fast and the place was full of happy, quiet people - no better sign of excellent food.

This place is a hidden gem. I ve lived a few blocks down from this place and walked by it almost every other day for like 8 years before I decided to walk in and check it out. They re so unassuming from the outside and inside is very basic too, but you ll find the best dumpling and noodle deal ever. It s waaaay better than these other dumpling spots in Chinatown and they re so authentic. Pretty sure they don t have fried dumplings though. But it s ok! They ve made me fall in love with boiled dumplings. And their peanut noodle and fish ball soup is delicious!
Great Dumplings

My go to place when I visit new york. The peanut noodles and dumplings are just delicious and awesomely priced for both $5 (peanut noodles $2 and dumplings $3)!  You get tons of food and great tasting food! This is not a place for people to sit down hours at a time. Be mindful that its a small restaurant with limited seating so if you come you either do take out or eat in and wait for whatever seat comes available. You order which comes out fast, find a seat, eat your food and leave don t linger around its not a starbucks be considerate to people who might be waiting for a seat!
Great food for a bargain in the heart of Chinatown in Manhattan.
Prices are unbelievably low. I had soup, dumplings and noodles for $6. Total. Cant say I loved the dishes but thats a matter of taste and it was all good.
Ive been coming here for several years. The quality of food stayed the same and still tastes great to this day. I typically order the peanut sauce noodles with dumpling soup and steamed dumplings

It is a tiny Fuzhou food place. Definitely it is not a perfect spot. They offer tasty fish balls, dumpling, and noodles here. Comparing to many stores in Chinatown, they have ample seating area. It can be pretty busy during the lunch and evening, but many people just stand there waiting for takeaway. Dont be scared.
Great food, seriously.  And the prices are unbeatable.  Also, for take-home: 50 (frozen) dumplings for $10.00.  Whattttt.
This place is No Frills. Good and cheap.
Best tasting wonton soup. Local Fujianese cuisine. Very authentic and delicious. Must try the Fujianese fish ball with stuffed meat.
The pork dumplings are fantastic. Note they are steamed only (but thats a good thing). Dont forget the wheat noodles in peanut butter sauce!
$3 peanut noodles are so good !!
The service attitude is rubbish. The food I ordered was ready and left there, but they wouldnt even call me. I had to go over and ask before they said yes, then it was gone, and they just said yes.
the peanut butter noodles is a must try
No-frills for sure, but I dont care. The peanut noodles are great. You might think what the heck are they?! at first. But they will grow on you so fast.
Very cheap noodles and dumplings.
Simple and very delicious.
If they served the peanut noodle dish at Nobo the price would be $24. Best noodle dish ive ever had. Its another level of food.

My favorite dumplings in Chinatown, hands down. They have really good peanut noodles and fishball soup as well. The staff is also friendly. If you have a hunger for simple, cheap, deliciois food - stop here!

If youre looking for ambiance candles and tablecloth, move on because theres nothing of that sort here.  Excellent taste and value.  If I were selfish Id give it fewer stars to keep the secret for myself.  The N.Y. daily news article is spot on.

The ones that are more expensive than it are not as delicious as this one. It is really delicious and cheap. I can t get tired of eating it every day. I highly recommend the flat pork (little chaos) and dumplings. Every time I go there, I will be very satisfied.

The dumplings are great and very very cheap, we tried a noddle dish with peanut sauce which was not much. The service is correct. The prices are incredible for 10 dollars for two people to dine. Drinks included.
detailed_reviews.review_translated_text: Los dumplings, son geniales y muy muy baratos, probamos un plato de noddle con salsa de cacahuete que no era gran cosa. El servicio es correcto. Los precios son increibles por 10 dolares cenamos dos personas. Bebidas incluidas.

detailed_reviews.review_text: Peanut noodles ($2) were a bit too watery and the pork wonton ($2) skins were a bit too firm but otherwise a good meal for a good price ($4).
An average store. . .
The best dumplings in New York hands down.
I literally go out of my way for their dumplings. Best prices for a great meal!

Great food, fast service, and excellent prices. I had a plate of dumplings for $3, pork ball soup for $2, can of soda for $1, and peanut noodles for $2. All of them tasted fresh and homemade. The portion are huge for the price. We couldnt finish all of our food but we all agreed that it is was excellent for the price. I will be coming back often for a cheap quick filling bite to eat!
Cheaper than Vanessas and bettee
Delicious cheap fujianese food
The ones that are cheaper than it are not as delicious as it, and the ones that are more delicious than it are not as cheap as it. In fact, this store is delicious and cheap!
Good dumplings and noodle dishes. One of the cheapest places around. You can get a meal for about $3. Nothing fancy about the decor here. Staff is friendly and will leave you alone while you eat.
Cheap ass delicious dumplings. Dont expect great service, just good dumplings and keep it moving
Awesome
Awesome dumplings and soups at amazing prices. Forget fancy brunch this is way better!
Dumplings were better than my grandmas
Always great food. Love their steam dumplings and beef tripe noodle soup. Cant beat their price. Affordable and delicious.
Go to dumpling and vegetarian spot Sour vegetable soup was great.
I get their dumplings, one of the best in the area. Doesnt leave may aftertaste like many others do.
Delicious chinese food.
Love this place. Delicious dumplings and soup at an unbeatable price
Looking for a cheap bite? Heres the place. 6 damn good dumplings for $3.
Super cheap and delicious.

5 star for its dumplings! Super cheap and delicious! Best dumplings Ive had in a while. The dumpling skin is not too soft after its cooked and it has a good amount of meat inside. Buy their frozen ones to take home, totally worth it!!! Its 50 dumplings for $10. Amazing! Both the chive and cabbage dumplings are equally yummy. The chive one has a heavier taste so if you prefer stronger tastes go with that one. Their peanut noodles are also really good but for some reason my noodles were too soft and overcooked. My friends was much better, more Al dente. Ill have to go back and try it again. I got 6 dumplings and a peanut noodle and it was only $4. Ridiculous!!! Where can you eat so much food for so cheap in Manhattan nowadays -- nowhere except here!
Soooo cheap and sooo good. The dumplings are addicting
Eat like a king for $5. Solid dumplings...forget Vanessas and come here instead! Peanut noodles are good too!
Cheap and good.  Best dumplings in LES.
Unbeatably cheap & tasty.
Literally like the best dumplings of all time.
Best boiled dumplings. Their soups and noodles are super cheap and tasty. Their peanut noodles are out of this world! I come here every week just for the noodles and dumplings.
Delicious cheap authentic food, and quick service.
Favorite snack spot on earth. Long summer weeks pinching pennies spent eating like a king here. Peanut noodles + dumplings +     is the perfect lunch.
Best place to go when on a budget..everything on the menu is less then $5..Love it
Great peanut noodles. Delicious pork and choice dumplings. Awesome late night snack.

This place was awesome. We got two beef tripe soups and two orders of dumplings (awesome BTW) and two drinks for $13 bucks! The food isnt really for the timid, but if youre willing to branch out a little bit its really good.
Cheap eats. No frills, nothing but delicious foods. Nice owner.
simply put, my favorite place to eat in NYC
Their dumplings hit the spot. One of the top places to get your dumpling fix.
Food is near dirt cheap and is always very tasty.

The best $8 date you will ever have. I ordered 20 dumplings and the peanut noodle dish to share with my date and it cost a whopping 8 bucks. So delicious. The dumplings (pork and chive) are very fresh, and the peanut noodle dish is the perfect balance of tangy, sweet and salty. The service is also super fast! Dont be discouraged by the look of the place--its a little dumpy-looking--but the food is so worth it.

10 ravioli + a dish of peanut butter noodles for $5. Very very fast service and very good food. I recommend.

Cash only! The pork and cabbage dumpling here is great (I prefer the boiled version over pan fried ones). The price is very cheap, and they also sell frozen dumplings at $8 for 50 pieces, which is quite a steal in my humble opinion!

Came here as the last stop on a dumpling crawl and ordered both the pork & chive and the pork & cabbage dumplings.  In order to enjoy the chive option, you have to really really really (did I say really?) like chives.  I thought I did, but this was a little too much for me and I did not enjoy them.  The pork & cabbage, however, had a great taste with well balanced flavors and a machined (i.e. thinner) skin, which I prefer.  Not a bad option for dumplings, especially if you like chives.

Solid hole-in-the-wall dumpling and noodle joint with rock-bottom prices. Some thought the pork & chive dumplings were too chive-y, but imo theres no such thing so I loved them. If youre sensitive to strong alliums, try the pork & cabbage dumplings instead. The peanut noodles here are also great.
Quality pork and chive boiled dumplings live in digs some may describe as sketchy or dingy. I call pure Chinatown.
Great food, prices and service. Just as good as lam zhou and better than vanessas for sure. The soup noodle is great too

They gave me a fork from the back. What I am saying is the customer service here is as good as there food. Which is wonderful. The pork dumplings are much more flavorful then Prosperity Dumplings are.

This place may look run down, but I assure you that the food is awesome. I got the peanut sauce noodles and dumplings. Those peanut noodles ... wow. If you love noodles, you must try this. The dumplings are good too. Prices are very cheap; you wont believe youre paying what theyre asking for. If you can tolerate the environment being on the dirtier, non-fancy side, definitely give this place a try. You wont regret it!

You know its good when the locals come here. Not the best date place.... then again who brings a date for dumplings but prices are good and food is made healthier than other places. Id rank this just behind prosperity dumplings and ahead of Vanessas. Plenty of room to sit. Its next door to Vanessas dumplings which is much cleaner but not as yummmy. Try then all
